msgid "<emphasis role=\"strong\">The Debian system does not pre-assign any special meaning differences among the <ulink url=\"&runlevels;\">runlevels</ulink> between 2 and 5.</emphasis> The system administrator on the Debian system may change this.  (I.e., Debian is not <ulink url=\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> nor <ulink url=\"&solarisbysunmicrosystems;\">Solaris by Sun Microsystems</ulink> nor <ulink url=\"&hpuxbyhewlettpackard;\">HP-UX by Hewlett Packard</ulink> nor <ulink url=\"&aixbyibm;\">AIX by IBM</ulink> nor …)"
msgstr "<emphasis role=\"strong\">Il sistema Debian non assegna nessuna differenza significativa ai<ulink url=\"&runlevels;\">runlevel</ulink> compresi tra 2 e 5.</emphasis> L'amministratore di un sistema Debian può cambiare questa situazione. (Cioè Debian non è <ulink url=\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> né <ulink url=\"&solarisbysunmicrosystems;\">Solaris di Sun Microsystems</ulink> né <ulink url=\"&hpuxbyhewlettpackard;\">HP-UX di Hewlett Packard</ulink> né <ulink url=\"&aixbyibm;\">AIX di IBM</ulink>, né …)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9682
msgid "The Debian system does not populate directories for the <ulink url=\"&runlevels;\">runlevels</ulink> between 7 and 9 when the package is installed.  Traditional <ulink url=\"&unixvariants;\">Unix variants</ulink> don’t use these <ulink url=\"&runlevels;\">runlevels</ulink>."
msgstr "Il sistema Debian non popola le directory per i <ulink url=\"&runlevels;\">runlevel</ulink> tra 7 e 9 quando il pacchetto è installato. Le <ulink url=\"&unixvariants;\">varianti di Unix</ulink> tradizionali non usano questi <ulink url=\"&runlevels;\">runlevel</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9686
msgid "The configuration of the runlevel"
msgstr "La configurazione del runlevel"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9688
msgid "In Debian <literal>squeeze</literal>, dependency based boot order provided by the <literal>insserv</literal> package is used instead of classical alphabetical one.  The \"<literal>CONCURRENCY</literal>\" value in \"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" controls its concurrency: \"<literal>none</literal>\" for no concurrency, \"<literal>startpar</literal>\" for concurrency within the same sequence number, or \"<literal>makefile</literal>\" for full concurrency.  See \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/insserv/README.Debian</literal>\"."
msgstr "In Debian <literal>squeeze</literal>, viene usato l'ordine di avvio basato sulle dipendenze fornito dal pacchetto <literal>insserv</literal>, invece di quello alfabetico classico. Il valore di \"<literal>CONCURRENCY</literal>\" in \"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" controlla la concorrenza: \"<literal>none</literal>\" per nessuna concorrenza, \"<literal>startpar</literal>\" per concorrenza con lo stesso numero di seuqenza o \"<literal>makefile</literal>\" per piena concorrenza. Vedere \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/insserv/README.Debian</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9690
msgid "The name of the symlink in each runlevel directory has the form \"<literal>S&lt;2-digit-number&gt;&lt;original-name&gt;</literal>\" or \"<literal>K&lt;2-digit-number&gt;&lt;original-name&gt;</literal>\". The 2-digit-number is used to determine the order in which to run the scripts. \"<literal>S</literal>\" is for \"Start\" and \"<literal>K</literal>\" is for \"Kill\"."
msgstr "Il nome dei collegamenti simbolici in ciascuna directory dei runlevel ha la forma \"<literal>S&lt;numero-a-2-cifre&gt;&lt;nome-originale&gt;</literal>\" o \"<literal>K&lt;numero-a-2-cifre&gt;&lt;nome-originale&gt;</literal>\". Il numero a due cifre è usato per determinare l'ordine in cui eseguire gli script. \"<literal>S</literal> sta per \"Start\" (avvia) e \"<literal>K</literal>\" sta per \"Kill\" (uccidi)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9691
msgid "For \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=none</literal>\", when <literal>init</literal>(8) or <literal>telinit</literal>(8) commands goes into the runlevel to \"&lt;n&gt;\", it execute following scripts."
msgstr "Con \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=none</literal>\", quando i comandi <literal>init</literal>(8) o <literal>telinit</literal>(8) vanno nel runlevel \"&lt;n&gt;\", eseguono gli script seguenti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9695
msgid "The script names starting with a \"<literal>K</literal>\" in \"<literal>/etc/rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal>\" are executed in alphabetical order with the single argument \"<literal>stop</literal>\". (killing services)"
msgstr "Gli script in \"<literal>/etc/rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal> il cui nome inizia con una \"<literal>K</literal>\" vengono eseguiti in ordine alfabetico con l'unico argomento \"<literal>stop</literal>\". (uccisione dei servizi)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9700
msgid "The script names starting with an \"<literal>S</literal>\" in \"<literal>/etc/rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal>\" are executed in alphabetical order with the single argument \"<literal>start</literal>\". (starting services)"
msgstr "Gli script in \"<literal>/etc/rc&lt;n&gt;.d/</literal> il cui nome inizia con una \"<literal>S</literal>\" vengono eseguiti in ordine alfabetico con l'unico argomento \"<literal>start</literal>\". (avvio dei servizi)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9704
msgid "For example, if you had the links \"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\" and \"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\" in a runlevel directory, \"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\" which is symlinked to \"<literal>../init.d/sysklogd</literal>\" would run before \"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\" which is symlinked to \"<literal>../init.d/exim4</literal>\"."
msgstr "Per esempio, se in una directory di runlevel sono presenti i collegamenti \"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\" e \"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\", \"<literal>S10sysklogd</literal>\", che è un collegamento simbolico a \"<literal>../init.d/sysklogd</literal>\", viene eseguito prima di \"<literal>S20exim4</literal>\", che è un collegamento simbolico a \"<literal>../init.d/exim4</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9705
msgid "For \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=makefile</literal>\" (new default), package dependency defined in the header of init scripts are used to order them."
msgstr "Con \"<literal>CONCURRENCY=makefile</literal>\" (nuovo valore predefinito), vengono usate le dipendenze di pacchetto definite nell'intestazione degli script init per ordinare la loro esecuzione."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9707
msgid "It is not advisable to make any changes to symlinks in \"<literal>/etc/rcS.d/</literal>\" unless you know better than the maintainer."
msgstr "È sconsigliato fare qualsiasi cambiamento ai collegamenti simbolici in \"<literal>/etc/rcS.d/</literal>\" a meno che non si sia più esperti del manutentore."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9711
msgid "The runlevel management example"
msgstr "Esempio di gestione dei runlevel"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9712
msgid "For example, let's set up runlevel system somewhat like <ulink url=\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> as the following."
msgstr "Per esempio, si può impostare il sistema dei runlevel in un modo che ricorda <ulink url=\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9715
msgid "<literal>init</literal> starts the system in runlevel=3 as the default."
msgstr "<literal>init</literal> avvia il sistema con runlevel=3 in modo predefinito."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9719
msgid "<literal>init</literal> does not start <literal>gdm</literal>(1) in runlevel=(0,1,2,6)."
msgstr "<literal>init</literal> non avvia <literal>gdm</literal>(1) nei runlevel=(0,1,2,6)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9723
msgid "<literal>init</literal> starts <literal>gdm</literal>(1) in runlevel=(3,4,5)."
msgstr "<literal>init</literal> avvia <literal>gdm</literal>(1) nei runlevel=(3,4,5)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9727
msgid "This can be done by using editor on the \"<literal>/etc/inittab</literal>\" file to change starting runlevel and using user friendly runlevel management tools such as <literal>sysv-rc-conf</literal> or <literal>bum</literal> to edit the runlevel.  If you are to use command line only instead, here is how you do it (after the default installation of the <literal>gdm</literal> package and selecting it to be the choice of display manager)."
msgstr "Si può ottenre questo modificando con un editor il file \"<literal>/etc/inittab</literal>\", per cambiare il runlevel di avvio, e usando strumenti amichevoli di gestione dei runlevel come <literal>sysv-rc-conf</literal> o <literal>bum</literal>, per modificare i runlevel. Se si vuole invece usare solamente la riga di comando, si può farlo nel modo seguente (dopo l'installazione standard del pacchetto <literal>gdm</literal> e avendolo selezionato come display manager prescelto)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9728
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /etc/rc2.d ; mv S21gdm K21gdm\n"
"# cd /etc ; perl -i -p -e 's/^id:.:/id:3:/' inittab"
msgstr ""
"# cd /etc/rc2.d ; mv S21gdm K21gdm\n"
"# cd /etc ; perl -i -p -e 's/^id:.:/id:3:/' inittab"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9730
msgid "Please note the \"<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</literal>\" file is checked when starting the display manager daemons: <literal>xdm</literal>, <literal>gdm</literal>, <literal>kdm</literal>, and <literal>wdm</literal>."
msgstr "Notare che il file \"<literal>/etc/X11/default-display-manager</literal>\" viene controllato quando vengono avviati i demoni per display manager: <literal>xdm</literal>, <literal>gdm</literal>, <literal>kdm</literal> e <literal>wdm</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9732
msgid "You can still start X from any console shell with the <literal>startx</literal>(1) command."
msgstr "Si può sempre avviare X da qualsiasi shell in console con il comando <literal>startx</literal>(1)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9736
msgid "The default parameter for each init script"
msgstr "Il parametro predefinito per ciascuno script init"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9737
msgid "The default parameter for each init script in \"<literal>/etc/init.d/</literal>\" is given by the corresponding file in \"<literal>/etc/default/</literal>\" which contains environment variable assignments <emphasis role=\"strong\">only</emphasis>. This choice of directory name is specific to the Debian system.  It is roughly the equivalent of the \"<literal>/etc/sysconfig</literal>\" directory found in <ulink url=\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> and other distributions.  For example, \"<literal>/etc/default/cron</literal>\" can be used to control how \"<literal>/etc/init.d/cron</literal>\" works."
msgstr "Il parametro predefinito per ciascun script init in \"<literal>/etc/init.d/</literal>\" è dato dal file corrispondente in \"<literal>/etc/default/</literal>\" che contiene <emphasis role=\"strong\">solamente</emphasis> assegnazioni di variabili d'ambiente. Il nome della directory è una scelta specifica di Debian. È grossomodo l'equivalente della directory \"<literal>/etc/sysconfig</literal>\" di <ulink url=\"&redhatlinux;\">Red Hat Linux</ulink> e altre distribuzioni. Per esempio, si può usare \"<literal>/etc/default/cron</literal>\" per controllare il funzionamento di \"<literal>/etc/init.d/cron</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9738
msgid "The \"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" file can be used to customize boot-time defaults for <literal>motd</literal>(5), <literal>sulogin</literal>(8), etc."
msgstr "Il file \"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" può essere usato per personalizzare impostazioni standard dell'avvio per <literal>motd</literal>(5), <literal>sulogin</literal>(8), ecc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9739
msgid "If you cannot get the behavior you want by changing such variables then you may <ulink url=\"&modifytheinitscripts;\">modify the init scripts</ulink> themselves.  These are configuration files editable by system administrators."
msgstr "Se non si ottiene il comportamento voluto cambiando queste variabili, si possono <ulink url=\"&modifytheinitscripts;\">modificare gli script init</ulink> stessi. Questi sono file di configurazione modificabili dall'amministratore di sistema."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9742
msgid "The hostname"
msgstr "Il nome host"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9743
msgid "The kernel maintains the system <emphasis role=\"strong\">hostname</emphasis>.  The init script in runlevel S which is symlinked to \"<literal>/etc/init.d/hostname.sh</literal>\" sets the system hostname at boot time (using the <literal>hostname</literal> command) to the name stored in \"<literal>/etc/hostname</literal>\".  This file should contain <emphasis role=\"strong\">only</emphasis> the system hostname, not a fully qualified domain name."
msgstr "Il kernel gestisce il <emphasis role=\"strong\">nome host</emphasis> del sistema. Lo script init nel runlevel S, che è un collegamento simbolico a \"<literal>/etc/init.d/hostname.sh</literal>\" imposta il nome host del sistema all'avvio (usando il comando <literal>hostname</literal>) al nome memorizzato in \"<literal>/etc/hostname</literal>\". Questo file dovrebbe contenere <emphasis role=\"strong\">solamente</emphasis> il nome host del sistema, non un nome di dominio pienamente qualificato."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9744
msgid "To print out the current hostname run <literal>hostname</literal>(1) without an argument."
msgstr "Per visualizzare il nome host attuale eseguire <literal>hostname</literal>(1) senza alcun argomento."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9747
msgid "The filesystem"
msgstr "Il filesystem"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9748
msgid "Although the root filesystem is mounted by the kernel when it is started, other filesystems are mounted in the runlevel S by the following init scripts."
msgstr "Benché il filesystem root sia montato dal kernel quando viene avviato, gli altri filesystem sono montati nel runlevel S dagli scritp init seguenti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9752
msgid "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountkernfs.sh</literal>\" for kernel filesystems in \"<literal>/proc</literal>\", \"<literal>/sys</literal>\", etc."
msgstr "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountkernfs.sh</literal>\" per i filesystem del kernel in \"<literal>/proc</literal>\", \"<literal>/sys</literal>\", ecc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9757
msgid "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountdevsubfs.sh</literal>\" for virtual filesystems in \"<literal>/dev</literal>\""
msgstr "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountdevsubfs.sh</literal>\" per i filesystem virtuali in \"<literal>/dev</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9762
msgid "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountall.sh</literal>\" for normal filesystems using \"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""
msgstr "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountall.sh</literal>\" per i filesystem normali, usando \"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9767
msgid "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountnfs.sh</literal>\" for network filesystems using\"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""
msgstr "\"<literal>`/etc/init.d/mountnfs.sh</literal>\" per i filesystem di rete, usando using\"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9771
msgid "The mount options of the filesystem are set in \"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\".  See <xref linkend=\"_optimization_of_filesystem_by_mount_options\"/>."
msgstr "Le opzioni usate per montare i filesystem sono impostate in \"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\". Vedere <xref linkend=\"_optimization_of_filesystem_by_mount_options\"/>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9773
msgid "The actual mounting of network filesystems waits for the start of the network interface."
msgstr "L'effettivo montaggio dei filesystem di rete attende l'avvio delle interfacce di rete."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9776
msgid "After mounting all the filesystems, temporary files in \"<literal>/tmp</literal>\", \"<literal>/var/lock</literal>\", and \"<literal>/var/run</literal>\" are cleaned for each boot up."
msgstr "Dopo aver montato tutti i filesystem, i file temporanei in \"<literal>/tmp</literal>\", \"<literal>/var/lock</literal>\" e \"<literal>/var/run</literal>\" vengono ripuliti ad ogni avvio."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9780
msgid "Network interface initialization"
msgstr "Inizializzazione delle interfacce di rete"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9781
msgid "Network interfaces are initialized in runlevel S by the init script symlinked to \"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown-clean</literal>\" and \"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown</literal>\".  See <xref linkend=\"_network_setup\"/> for how to configure them."
msgstr "Le interfacce di rete sono inizializzate nel runlevel S dagli script init che sono collegamenti simbolici a \"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown-clean</literal>\" e \"<literal>/etc/init.d/ifupdown</literal>\". Vedere<xref linkend=\"_network_setup\"/> per la loro configurazione."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9784
msgid "Network service initialization"
msgstr "Inizializzazione dei servizi di rete"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9785
msgid "Many network services (see <xref linkend=\"_network_applications\"/>) are started under multi-user mode directly as daemon processes at boot time by the init script, e.g., \"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20exim4</literal>\" (for RUNLEVEL=2) which is a symlink to \"<literal>/etc/init.d/exim4</literal>\"."
msgstr "Molti servizi di rete (vedere <xref linkend=\"_network_applications\"/>) sono avviati nella modalità multi-utente direttamente, come processi demone, all'avvio da script di init, per esempio, \"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20exim4</literal>\" (per RUNLEVEL=2) che è un collegamento simbolico a \"<literal>/etc/init.d/exim4</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9786
msgid "Some network services can be started on demand using the <ulink url=\"&superserver;\">super-server</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal> (or its equivalents).  The <literal>inetd</literal> is started at boot time by \"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20inetd</literal>\" (for RUNLEVEL=2) which is a symlink to \"<literal>/etc/init.d/inetd</literal>\".  Essentially, <literal>inetd</literal> allows one running daemon to invoke several others, reducing load on the system."
msgstr "Alcuni servizi di rete possono essere avviati a richiesta, usando il <ulink url=\"&superserver;\">super-server</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal> (o un equivalente). <literal>inetd</literal> viene avviato all'avvio da \"<literal>/etc/rc2.d/S20inetd</literal>\" (per RUNLEVEL=2) che è un collegamento simbolico a \"<literal>/etc/init.d/inetd</literal>\". Fondamentalmente <literal>inetd</literal> permette ad un demone in esecuzione di invocarne svariati altri, riducendo il carico sul sistema."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9787
msgid "Whenever a request for service arrives at <ulink url=\"&superserver;\">super-server</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal> , its protocol and service are identified by looking them up in the databases in \"<literal>/etc/protocols</literal>\" and \"<literal>/etc/services</literal>\".  <literal>inetd</literal> then looks up a normal Internet service in the \"<literal>/etc/inetd.conf</literal>\" database, or a <ulink url=\"&opennetworkcompucalloncrpcsunrpc;\">Open Network Computing Remote Procedure Call (ONC RPC)/Sun RPC</ulink> based service in \"<literal>/etc/rpc.conf</literal>\"."
msgstr "Quando al <ulink url=\"&superserver;\">super-server</ulink> <literal>inetd</literal> arriva una richiesta per un servizio, vengono identificati il suo protocollo e il suo servizio cercandoli nei database in \"<literal>/etc/protocols</literal>\" e \"<literal>/etc/services</literal>\". <literal>inetd</literal> quindi cerca un servizio Internet normale nel database \"<literal>/etc/inetd.conf</literal>\" o un servizio basato su  <ulink url=\"&opennetworkcompucalloncrpcsunrpc;\">Open Network Computing Remote Procedure Call (ONC RPC)/Sun RPC</ulink> in \"<literal>/etc/rpc.conf</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9788
msgid "Sometimes, <literal>inetd</literal> does not start the intended server directly but starts the <ulink url=\"&tcpwrapper;\">TCP wrapper</ulink> program, <literal>tcpd</literal>(8), with the intended server name as its argument in \"<literal>/etc/inetd.conf</literal>\".  In this case, <literal>tcpd</literal> runs the appropriate server program after logging the request and doing some additional checks using \"<literal>/etc/hosts.deny</literal>\" and \"<literal>/etc/hosts.allow</literal>\"."
msgstr "A volte, <literal>inetd</literal> non avvia il servizio richiesto direttamente, ma avvia il programma <ulink url=\"&tcpwrapper;\">wrapper TCP</ulink> <literal>tcpd</literal>(8), con il nome di servizio richiesto, in \"<literal>/etc/inetd.conf</literal>\", come argomento. In questo caso, <literal>tcpd</literal> esegue il programma server appropriato dopo aver fatto la registrazione della richiesta e qualche altro controllo addizionale usando \"<literal>/etc/hosts.deny</literal>\" e \"<literal>/etc/hosts.allow</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9789
msgid "For system security, disable as much network service programs as possible.  See <xref linkend=\"_restricting_access_to_some_server_services\"/>."
msgstr "Per la sicurezza del sistema è bene disabilitare più servizi di rete possibile. Vedere <xref linkend=\"_restricting_access_to_some_server_services\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9790
msgid "See <literal>inetd</literal>(8), <literal>inetd.conf</literal>(5), <literal>protocols</literal>(5), <literal>services</literal>(5), <literal>tcpd</literal>(8), <literal>hosts_access</literal>(5), <literal>hosts_options</literal>(5), <literal>rpcinfo</literal>(8), <literal>portmap</literal>(8), and \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/portmap/portmapper.txt.gz</literal>\"."
msgstr "Vedere <literal>inetd</literal>(8), <literal>inetd.conf</literal>(5), <literal>protocols</literal>(5), <literal>services</literal>(5), <literal>tcpd</literal>(8), <literal>hosts_access</literal>(5), <literal>hosts_options</literal>(5), <literal>rpcinfo</literal>(8), <literal>portmap</literal>(8) e \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/portmap/portmapper.txt.gz</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9793
msgid "The system message"
msgstr "I messaggi di sistema"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:9794
