#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12776
msgid "The PPP connection"
msgstr "Connessione PPP"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12777
msgid "You need to configure the PPP connection first as described before (see <xref linkend=\"_the_ppp_connection_with_pppconfig\"/>).  Then, add the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file entry for the primary PPP device <literal>ppp0</literal> as the following."
msgstr "È necessario come prima cosa configurare la connessione PPP come descritto in precedenza (vedere <xref linkend=\"_the_ppp_connection_with_pppconfig\"/>). Quindi aggiungere nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" la voce per il device PPP primario <literal>ppp0</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12778
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"iface ppp0 inet ppp\n"
" provider &lt;isp_name&gt;"
msgstr ""
"iface ppp0 inet ppp\n"
" provider &lt;nome_isp&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12782
msgid "The alternative PPP connection"
msgstr "Connessione PPP alternativa"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12783
msgid "You need to configure the alternative PPP connection with <literal>wvdial</literal> first as described before (see <xref linkend=\"_the_alternative_ppp_connection_with_wvdialconf\"/>).  Then, add the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file entry for the primary PPP device <literal>ppp0</literal> as the following."
msgstr "È necessario come prima cosa configurare la connessione PPP alternativa con <literal>wvdial</literal>, come descritto in precedenza (vedere <xref linkend=\"_the_alternative_ppp_connection_with_wvdialconf\"/>). Quindi aggiungere nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" la voce per il device PPP primario <literal>ppp0</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12784
#, no-wrap
msgid "iface ppp0 inet wvdial"
msgstr "iface ppp0 inet wvdial"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12787
msgid "The PPPoE connection"
msgstr "Connessione PPPoE"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12788
msgid "For PC connected directly to the WAN served by the PPPoE, you need to configure system with the PPPoE connection as described before (see <xref linkend=\"_the_pppoe_connection_with_pppoeconf\"/>).  Then, add the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file entry for the primary PPPoE device <literal>eth0</literal> as the following."
msgstr "Per i PC connessi direttamente alla WAN con servizio PPPoE, è necessario configurare il sistema con la connessione PPPoE come descritto in precedenza (vedere <xref linkend=\"_the_pppoe_connection_with_pppoeconf\"/>). Quindi aggiungere nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" la voce per il device PPPoE primario <literal>eth0</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12789
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet manual\n"
" pre-up /sbin/ifconfig eth0 up\n"
" up ifup ppp0=dsl\n"
" down ifdown ppp0=dsl\n"
" post-down /sbin/ifconfig eth0 down\n"
"# The following is used internally only\n"
"iface dsl inet ppp\n"
" provider dsl-provider"
msgstr ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet manual\n"
" pre-up /sbin/ifconfig eth0 up\n"
" up ifup ppp0=dsl\n"
" down ifdown ppp0=dsl\n"
" post-down /sbin/ifconfig eth0 down\n"
"# Quello che segue e' usato solo internamente\n"
"iface dsl inet ppp\n"
" provider dsl-provider"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12800
msgid "The network configuration state of ifupdown"
msgstr "Lo stato di configurazione della rete di ifupdown"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12801
msgid "The \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file stores the <emphasis role=\"strong\">intended</emphasis> network configuration states for all the currently active network interfaces managed by the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package are listed. Unfortunately, even if the <literal>ifupdown</literal> system fails to bring up the interface as intended, the \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file lists it active."
msgstr "Il file \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" memorizza gli stati <emphasis role=\"strong\">previsti</emphasis> di configurazione della rete per tutte le interfacce di rete attualmente attive gestite dal pacchetto<literal>ifupdown</literal>. Sfortunatamente, anche se il tentativo del sistema <literal>ifupdown</literal> di attivare un'interfaccia come previsto fallisce, il file \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" la elenca come attiva."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12802
msgid "Unless the output of the <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) command for an interface does not have a line like following example, it can not be used as a part of <ulink url=\"&ipvenetwork;\">IPV4 network</ulink>."
msgstr "Se l'output del comando <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) per un'interfaccia non ha una riga come quella dell'esempio seguente, l'interfaccia non può essere usata come parte di una <ulink url=\"&ipvenetwork;\">rete IPV4</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12803
#, no-wrap
msgid "  inet addr:192.168.11.2  Bcast:192.168.11.255  Mask:255.255.255.0"
msgstr "  inet addr:192.168.11.2  Bcast:192.168.11.255  Mask:255.255.255.0"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12805
msgid "For the Ethernet device connected to the PPPoE, the output of the <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) command lacks a line which looks like above example."
msgstr "Per i dispositivi Ethernet connessi con PPPoE, l'output di <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) manca di una riga come quella dell'esempio precedente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12809
msgid "The basic network reconfiguration"
msgstr "Riconfigurazione base della rete"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12810
msgid "When you try to reconfigure the interface, e.g. <literal>eth0</literal>, you must disable it first with the \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0</literal></emphasis>\" command.  This removes the entry of <literal>eth0</literal> from the \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file. (This may result in some error message if <literal>eth0</literal> is not active or it is configured improperly previously.  So far, it seems to be safe to do this for the simple single user work station at any time.)"
msgstr "Quando si cerca di riconfigurare un'interfaccia, ad esempio <literal>eth0</literal>, per prima cosa è necessario disattivarla con il comando \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0</literal></emphasis>\". Questo rimuove la voce corrispondente ad <literal>eth0</literal> dal file \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\". (Potrebbero essere generati messaggi di errore se <literal>eth0</literal> non è attiva o se non era stata configurata in modo conrretto.) Per il momento, fare questa azione per una postazione di lavoro per singolo utente sembra sicuro in qualunque momento."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12811
msgid "You are now free to rewrite the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" contents as needed to reconfigure the network interface, <literal>eth0</literal>."
msgstr "Si può ora modificare liberamente il contenuto di \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" in base alle proprie necessità per riconfigurare l'interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12812
msgid "Then, you can reactivate <literal>eth0</literal> with the \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>\" command."
msgstr "In seguito si può riattivare <literal>eth0</literal> con il comando \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12814
msgid "You can (re)initialize the network interface simply by \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0;sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>\"."
msgstr "Si può (re)inizializzare l'interfaccia di rete semplicemente usando \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0;sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12818
msgid "The ifupdown-extra package"
msgstr "Pacchetto ifupdown-extra"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12819
msgid "The <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> package provides easy network connection tests for use with the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package."
msgstr "Il pacchetto <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> fornisce facili testi della connessione di rete per l'uso con il pacchetto <literal>ifupdown</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12823
msgid "The <literal>network-test</literal>(1) command can be used from the shell."
msgstr "Il comando <literal>network-test</literal>(1) può essere usato dalla shell."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12828
msgid "The automatic scripts are run for each <literal>ifup</literal> command execution."
msgstr "Gli script automatici vengono eseguiti per ogni invocazione del comando <literal>ifup</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12832
msgid "The <literal>network-test</literal> command frees you from the execution of cumbersome low level commands to analyze the network problem."
msgstr "Il comando <literal>network-test</literal> libera l'utente dal faticoso compito di eseguire comandi a basso livello per analizzare i problemi di rete."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12833
msgid "The automatic scripts are installed in \"<literal>/etc/network/*/</literal>\" and performs the following."
msgstr "Gli script automtici vengono installati in \"<literal>/etc/network/*/</literal>\" e effettuano le azioni seguenti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12837
msgid "Check the network cable connection"
msgstr "Verifica della connessione del cavo di rete"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12842
msgid "Check duplicate use of IP address"
msgstr "Verifica dell'eventuale uso duplicato di indirizzi IP"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12847
msgid "Setup system's static routes based on the \"<literal>/etc/network/routes</literal>\" definition"
msgstr "Impostazione di instradamenti statici del sistema in base alle definizioni in \"<literal>/etc/network/routes</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12852
msgid "Check if network gateway is reachable"
msgstr "Verifica della raggiungibilità del gateway di rete"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12857
msgid "Record results in the \"<literal>/var/log/syslog</literal>\" file"
msgstr "Registrazione dei risultati nel file \"<literal>/var/log/syslog</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12861
msgid "This syslog record is quite useful for administration of the network problem on the remote system."
msgstr "Queste voci nel syslog sono piuttosto utili per l'amministrazione di problemi di rete nel sistema remoto."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12863
msgid "The automatic behavior of the <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> package is configurable with the \"<literal>/etc/default/network-test</literal>\". Some of these automatic checks slow down the system boot-up a little bit since it takes some time to listen for <ulink url=\"&arp;\">ARP</ulink> replies."
msgstr "Il comportamento automatico del pacchetto <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> è configurabile con \"<literal>/etc/default/network-test</literal>\". Alcuni di questi controlli automatici rallentano un po' il sistema all'avvio dato che è necessario un po' di tempo per restare in ascolto per le risposte <ulink url=\"&arp;\">ARP</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12868
msgid "The advanced network configuration with ifupdown (legacy)"
msgstr "Configurazione avanzata della rete con ifupdown (strumento datato)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12869
msgid "The functionality of the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package can be improved beyond what was described in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/> with the advanced knowledge."
msgstr "Le funzionalità del pacchetto  <literal>ifupdown</literal> possono essere migliorate andando oltre quanto è stato descritto in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/>, con qualche informazione più avanzata."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12870
msgid "The functionalities described here are completely optional.  I, being lazy and minimalist, rarely bother to use these."
msgstr "Le funzionalità descritte in questa sezione sono completamente opzionali. Essendo io pigro e minimalista, raramente faccio lo sforzo di usarle."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12872
msgid "If you could not set up network connection by information in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/>, you make situation worse by using information below."
msgstr "Se non si è riusciti a configurare la connessione di rete usando le informazioni in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/>, cercare una soluzione nelle informazioni che seguono non farà che peggiorare le cose."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12875
msgid "The ifplugd package"
msgstr "Il pacchetto ifplugd"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12876
msgid "The <literal>ifplugd</literal> package is older automatic network configuration tool which can manage only Ethernet connections. This solves unplugged/replugged Ethernet cable issues for mobile PC etc.  If you have <ulink url=\"&networkmanager;\">NetworkManager</ulink> or <ulink url=\"&wicd;\">Wicd</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_the_modern_network_configuration_for_desktop\"/>) installed, you do not need this package."
msgstr "Il pacchetto <literal>ifplugd</literal> è un vecchio strumento di configurazione della rete che può gestire soltanto connessioni Ethernet. Risolve problemi di cavi Ethernet sconnessi/ricconessi per PC portatili, ecc. Se è installato <ulink url=\"&networkmanager;\">NetworkManager</ulink> o <ulink url=\"&wicd;\">Wicd</ulink> (vedere <xref linkend=\"_the_modern_network_configuration_for_desktop\"/>), questo pacchetto non è necessario."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12877
msgid "This package runs <ulink url=\"&daemon;\">daemon</ulink> and replaces <emphasis role=\"strong\">auto</emphasis> or <emphasis role=\"strong\">allow-hotplug</emphasis> functionalities (see <xref linkend=\"list-of-stanzas-in-eni\"/>) and starts interfaces upon their connection to the network."
msgstr "Questo pacchetto viene eseguito come <ulink url=\"&daemon;\">demone</ulink> e rimpiazza le funzionalità <emphasis role=\"strong\">auto</emphasis> o <emphasis role=\"strong\">allow-hotplug</emphasis> (vedere <xref linkend=\"list-of-stanzas-in-eni\"/>) ed abilita le interfacce quando queste vengono connesse alla rete."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12878
msgid "Here is how to use the <literal>ifplugd</literal> package for the internal Ethernet port, e.g. <literal>eth0</literal>."
msgstr "Ecco come usare il pacchetto <literal>ifplugd</literal> per la porta Ethernet interna, ad esempio <literal>eth0</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12882
msgid "Remove stanza in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\": \"<literal>auto eth0</literal>\" or \"<literal>allow-hotplug eth0</literal>\"."
msgstr "Rimuovere il blocco \"<literal>auto eth0</literal>\" o \"<literal>allow-hotplug eth0</literal>\" dal file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12887
msgid "Keep stanza in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\": \"<literal>iface eth0 inet …</literal>\" and \"<literal>mapping …</literal>\"."
msgstr "Mantenere i blocchi \"<literal>iface eth0 inet …</literal>\" e \"<literal>mapping …</literal>\" nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12892
msgid "Install the <literal>ifplugd</literal> package."
msgstr "Installare il pacchetto <literal>ifplugd</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12897
msgid "Run \"<literal>sudo dpkg-reconfigure ifplugd</literal>\"."
msgstr "Eseguire \"<literal>sudo dpkg-reconfigure ifplugd</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12902
msgid "Put <literal>eth0</literal> as the \"static interfaces to be watched by ifplugd\"."
msgstr "Indicare <literal>eth0</literal> come \"interfaccia statica che ifplugd deve osservare\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12906
msgid "Now, the network reconfiguration works as you desire."
msgstr "Ora, dopo la riconfigurazione, la rete funziona come voluto."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12910
msgid "Upon power-on or upon hardware discovery, the interface is not brought up by itself."
msgstr "All'avvio o al rilevamento dell'hardware, l'interfaccia non viene attivata da sé stessa."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12915
msgid "Quick boot process without the long DHCP timeout."
msgstr "Procedura di avvio veloce senza lunghi tempi di attesa per DHCP."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12920
msgid "No funny activated interface without proper IPv4 address (see <xref linkend=\"_the_network_configuration_state_of_ifupdown\"/>)."
msgstr "Nessuna interfaccia attivata in modo inconsueto senza un appropriato indirizzo IPv4 (vedere <xref linkend=\"_the_network_configuration_state_of_ifupdown\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12927
msgid "Upon finding the Ethernet cable, the interface is brought up."
msgstr "Quando viene rilevato il cavo Ethernet l'interfaccia viene attivata."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12932
msgid "Upon some time after unplugging the Ethernet cable, the interface is brought down automatically."
msgstr "Dopo un certo intervallo di tempo dalla disconnessione del cavo Ethernet, l'interfaccia viene automaticamente disattivata."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12937
msgid "Upon plugging in another Ethernet cable, the interface is brought up under the new network environment."
msgstr "Quando viene inserito un altro cavo Ethernet, l'interfaccia è attivata nel nuovo ambiente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12942
msgid "The arguments for the <literal>ifplugd</literal>(8) command can set its behaviors such as the delay for reconfiguring interfaces."
msgstr "Gli argomenti del comando <literal>ifplugd</literal>(8) possono impostare il suo comportamento, come il ritardo nella riconfigurazione delle interfacce."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12946
msgid "The ifmetric package"
msgstr "Il pacchetto ifmetric"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12947
msgid "The <literal>ifmeric</literal> package enables us to manipulate metrics of routes a posteriori even for DHCP."
msgstr "Il pacchetto <literal>ifmetric</literal> permette di manipolare la metrica di instradamenti a posteriori, anche per DHCP."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12948
msgid "The following sets the <literal>eth0</literal> interface to be preferred over the <literal>wlan0</literal> interface."
msgstr "Le azioni seguenti impostano l'interfaccia <literal>eth0</literal> come preferita rispetto alla interfaccia <literal>wlan0</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12952
msgid "Install the <literal>ifmetric</literal> package."
msgstr "Installare il pacchetto <literal>ifmetric</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12957
msgid "Add an option line with \"<literal>metric 0</literal>\" just below the \"<literal>iface eth0 inet dhcp</literal>\" line."
msgstr "Aggiungere una riga con l'opzione \"<literal>metric 0</literal>\" immediatamente sotto alla riga \"<literal>iface eth0 inet dhcp</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12962
msgid "Add an option line with \"<literal>metric 1</literal>\" just below the \"<literal>iface wlan0 inet dhcp</literal>\" line."
msgstr "Aggiungere una riga con l'opzione \"<literal>metric 1</literal>\" immediatamente sotto alla riga \"<literal>iface wlan0 inet dhcp</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12966
msgid "The metric 0 means the highest priority route and is the default one.  The larger metric value means lower priority routes. The IP address of the active interface with the lowest metric value becomes the originating one. See <literal>ifmetric</literal>(8)."
msgstr "\"metric 0\" significa instradamento con la più alta priorità ed è quello predefinito. Un valore di metrica più alto indica instradamenti con priorità più bassa. L'indirizzo IP dell'interfaccia attiva con il valore di metrica più basso diventa quello di origine. Vedere <literal>ifmetric</literal>(8)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12969
msgid "The virtual interface"
msgstr "L'interfaccia virtuale"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12970
msgid "A single physical Ethernet interface can be configured as multiple virtual interfaces with different IP addresses.  Usually the purpose is to connect an interface to several IP subnetworks.  For example, IP address based virtual web hosting by a single network interface is one such application."
msgstr "Una singola interfaccia fisica Ethernet può essere configurata come interfacce virtuali multiple con indirizzi IP differenti. Di solito ciò ha lo scopo di connettere un'interfaccia a diverse sottoreti di IP. Per esempio, un'applicazione di questo tipo è l'hosting web virtuale basato su indirizzi IP con una singola interfaccia di rete."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12971
msgid "For example, let's suppose the following."
msgstr "Per esempio, si supponga quanto segue."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12975
msgid "A single Ethernet interface on your host is connected to a Ethernet hub (not to the broadband router)."
msgstr "Una singola interfaccia Ethernet dell'host è connessa ad un hub Ethernet (non al router a banda larga)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12980
msgid "The Ethernet hub is connected to both the Internet and LAN network."
msgstr "L'hub Ethernet è connesso sia ad Internet sia alla rete LAN."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12985
msgid "The LAN network uses subnet <literal>192.168.0.x/24</literal>."
msgstr "La rete LAN usa la sottorete <literal>192.168.0.x/24</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12990
msgid "Your host uses DHCP served IP address with the physical interface <literal>eth0</literal> for the Internet."
msgstr "L'host usa per Internet indirizzi IP DHCP sull'interfaccia fisica <literal>eth0</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12995
msgid "Your host uses <literal>192.168.0.1</literal> with the virtual interface <literal>eth0:0</literal> for the LAN."
msgstr "L'host usa <literal>192.168.0.1</literal> con l'interfaccia virtuale <literal>eth0:0</literal> per la LAN."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12999
msgid "The following stanzas in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" configure your network."
msgstr "I blocchi seguenti in \" <literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" configurano la rete."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13000
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
" metric 0\n"
"iface eth0:0 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.0.1\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" network 192.168.0.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.0.255\n"
" metric 1"
msgstr ""
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
" metric 0\n"
"iface eth0:0 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.0.1\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" network 192.168.0.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.0.255\n"
" metric 1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13009
msgid "Although this configuration example with <ulink url=\"&networkaddresstranslationnat;\">network address translation (NAT)</ulink> using <ulink url=\"&netfilteriptables;\">netfilter/iptables</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_netfilter_infrastructure\"/>) can provide cheap router for the LAN with only single interface, there is no real firewall capability with such set up.  You should use 2 physical interfaces with NAT to secure the local network from the Internet."
msgstr "Anche se questo esempio di configurazione con <ulink url=\"&networkaddresstranslationnat;\">traduzione degli indirizzi di rete (NAT)</ulink> usando <ulink url=\"&netfilteriptables;\">netfilter/iptables</ulink> (vedere <xref linkend=\"_netfilter_infrastructure\"/>) può fornire un router a basso prezzo per la LAN usando una sola interfaccia, non c'è alcuna reale funzionalità di firewall con una configurazione di questo tipo. Si dovrebbero usare 2 interfacce fisiche con NAT per rendere sicura la rete locale rispetto ad Internet."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13013
msgid "The advanced command syntax"
msgstr "Sintassi avanzata dei comandi"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13014
msgid "The <literal>ifupdown</literal> package offers advanced network configuration using the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name and the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> name.  I use slightly different terminology from one used in <literal>ifup</literal>(8) and <literal>interfaces</literal>(5)."
msgstr "Il pacchetto <literal>ifupdown</literal> offre funzionalità di configurazione avanzata della rete usando il nome di <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione della rete</emphasis> e il nome dell'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis>. Viene qui usata una terminologia leggermente diversa da quella usata in <literal>ifup</literal>(8) e <literal>interfaces</literal>(5)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13016
msgid "List of terminology for network devices"
msgstr "Elenco della terminologia per i device di rete"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13025
msgid "manpage terminology"
msgstr "terminologia delle pagine man"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13028
msgid "my terminology"
msgstr "terminologia di questo documento"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13031
msgid "examples in the following text"
msgstr "esempi nel testo seguente"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13040
msgid "<emphasis role=\"strong\">physical interface</emphasis> name"
msgstr "nome dell'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia fisica</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13042
msgid "<emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> name"
msgstr "nome dell'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13044
msgid "<literal>lo</literal>, <literal>eth0</literal>, <literal>&lt;interface_name&gt;</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>lo</literal>, <literal>eth0</literal>, <literal>&lt;nome_interfaccia&gt;</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13046
msgid "name given by the Linux kernel (using <literal>udev</literal> mechanism)"
msgstr "nome dato dal kernel Linux (usando il meccanismo <literal>udev</literal>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13050
msgid "<emphasis role=\"strong\">logical interface</emphasis> name"
msgstr "nome dell'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia logica</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13052
msgid "<emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name"
msgstr "nome della <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione di rete</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13054
msgid "<literal>config1</literal>, <literal>config2</literal>, <literal>&lt;config_name&gt;</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>config1</literal>, <literal>config2</literal>, <literal>&lt;nome_config&gt;</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13056
msgid "name token following <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\""
msgstr "elemento indicante il nome che segue la parola <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13062
msgid "Basic network configuration commands in <xref linkend=\"_the_command_syntax_simplified\"/> require the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name token of the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> stanza to match the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> name in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\"."
msgstr "I comandi base per la configurazione della rete descritti in <xref linkend=\"_the_command_syntax_simplified\"/> richiedono che, nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\", il nome della <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione di rete</emphasis> indicato nel blocco <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> corrisponda al nome dell'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13063
msgid "Advanced network configuration commands enables separation of the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name and the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> name in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" as the following."
msgstr "I comandi avanzati per la configurazione della rete permettono, nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\", la distinzione tra il nome della <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione di rete</emphasis> e della <emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis> "

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13065
msgid "List of advanced network configuration commands with ifupdown"
msgstr "Elenco di comandi avanzati per la configurazione della rete con ifupdown"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13082
msgid "<literal>ifup eth0=config1</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>ifup eth0=config1</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13085
msgid "bring up a network interface <literal>eth0</literal> with the configuration <literal>config1</literal>"
msgstr "attiva una interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> con la configurazione <literal>config1</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13090
msgid "<literal>ifdown eth0=config1</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>ifdown eth0=config1</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13093
msgid "bring down a network interface <literal>eth0</literal> with the configuration <literal>config1</literal>"
msgstr "disattiva una interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> con la configurazione <literal>config1</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13101
msgid "bring up a network interface <literal>eth0</literal> with the configuration selected by <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> stanza"
msgstr "attiva una interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> con la configurazione scelta dal blocco di mappatura <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13109
msgid "bring down a network interface <literal>eth0</literal> with the configuration selected by <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> stanza"
msgstr "disattiva una interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> con la configurazione scelta dal blocco di mappatura <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13117
msgid "The mapping stanza"
msgstr "Il blocco di mappatura \"mapping\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13118
msgid "We skipped explaining the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> stanza in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_syntax_of_etc_network_interfaces\"/> to avoid complication.  This stanza has the following syntax."
msgstr "Nella sezione <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_syntax_of_etc_network_interfaces\"/> è stata saltata la spiegazione del blocco <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\", per evitare complicazioni. Questo blocco ha la sintassi seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13119
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mapping &lt;interface_name_glob&gt;\n"
" script &lt;script_name&gt;\n"
" map &lt;script_input1&gt;\n"
" map &lt;script_input2&gt;\n"
" map ..."
msgstr ""
"mapping &lt;glob_nome_interfaccia&gt;\n"
" script &lt;nome_script&gt;\n"
" map &lt;script_input1&gt;\n"
" map &lt;script_input2&gt;\n"
" map ..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13124
msgid "This provides advanced feature to the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file by automating the choice of the configuration with the mapping script specified by <literal>&lt;script_name&gt;</literal>."
msgstr "Ciò fornisce funzionalità avanzate al file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" automatizzando la scelta della configurazione con lo script di mappatura specificato da <literal>&lt;nome_script&gt;</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13125
msgid "Let's follow the execution of the following."
msgstr "Ecco cosa succede quando viene eseguito il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13126
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo ifup eth0"
msgstr "$ sudo ifup eth0"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13127
msgid "When the \"<literal>&lt;interface_name_glob&gt;</literal>\" matches \"<literal>eth0</literal>\", this execution produces the execution of the following command to configure <literal>eth0</literal> automatically."
msgstr "Quando il \"<literal>&lt;glob_nome_interfaccia&gt;</literal> trova corrispondenza con \"<literal>eth0</literal>\", l'esecuzione di questo comando produce, per configurare automaticamente <literal>eth0</literal>,  l'invocazione del comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13128
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo ifup eth0=$(echo -e '&lt;script_input1&gt; \\n &lt;script_input2&gt; \\n ...' | &lt;script_name&gt; eth0)"
msgstr "$ sudo ifup eth0=$(echo -e '&lt;script_input1&gt; \\n &lt;script_input2&gt; \\n ...' | &lt;nome_script&gt; eth0)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13129
msgid "Here, script input lines with \"<literal>map</literal>\" are optional and can be repeated."
msgstr "Le righe, per l'input dello script, che iniziano con \"<literal>map</literal>\" sono opzionali e possono essere ripetute."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13131
msgid "The glob for <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> stanza works like shell filename glob (see <xref linkend=\"_shell_glob\"/>)."
msgstr "L'espressione glob per il blocco <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> funziona come i metacaratteri dei glob per nomi di file della shell (vedere <xref linkend=\"_shell_glob\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13135
msgid "The manually switchable network configuration"
msgstr "Configurazione della rete commutabile manualmente"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13136
msgid "Here is how to switch manually among several network configurations without rewriting the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file as in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_reconfiguration\"/> ."
msgstr "Quella che segue è una descrizione di come commutare manualmente tra diverse configurazioni di rete senza dover riscrivere il file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" come in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_reconfiguration\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13137
msgid "For all the network configuration you need to access, you create a single \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Per tutte le configurazioni di rete alle quali si deve accedere è sufficiente creare un solo file \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" come quello seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13138
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"auto lo\n"
"iface lo inet loopback\n"
"\n"
"iface config1 inet dhcp\n"
" hostname \"mymachine\"\n"
"\n"
"iface config2 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.11.100\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.11.255\n"
" gateway 192.168.11.1\n"
" dns-domain lan\n"
" dns-nameservers 192.168.11.1\n"
"\n"
"iface pppoe inet manual\n"
" pre-up /sbin/ifconfig eth0 up\n"
" up ifup ppp0=dsl\n"
" down ifdown ppp0=dsl\n"
" post-down /sbin/ifconfig eth0 down\n"
"\n"
"# The following is used internally only\n"
"iface dsl inet ppp\n"
" provider dsl-provider\n"
"\n"
"iface pots inet ppp\n"
" provider provider"
msgstr ""
"auto lo\n"
"iface lo inet loopback\n"
"\n"
"iface config1 inet dhcp\n"
" hostname \"miamacchina\"\n"
"\n"
"iface config2 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.11.100\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.11.255\n"
" gateway 192.168.11.1\n"
" dns-domain lan\n"
" dns-nameservers 192.168.11.1\n"
"\n"
"iface pppoe inet manual\n"
" pre-up /sbin/ifconfig eth0 up\n"
" up ifup ppp0=dsl\n"
" down ifdown ppp0=dsl\n"
" post-down /sbin/ifconfig eth0 down\n"
"\n"
"# Quello che segue e' usato solo internamente\n"
"iface dsl inet ppp\n"
" provider dsl-provider\n"
"\n"
"iface pots inet ppp\n"
" provider provider"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13164
msgid "Please note the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration name</emphasis> which is the token after <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> does not use the token for the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface name</emphasis>.  Also, there are no <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>auto</literal></emphasis> stanza nor <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>allow-hotplug</literal></emphasis> stanza to start the network interface <literal>eth0</literal> automatically upon events."
msgstr "Notare che il <emphasis role=\"strong\">nome di configurazione della rete</emphasis>, che è l'elemento che viene dopo <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis>, non usa il <emphasis role=\"strong\">nome dell'interfaccia di rete</emphasis>. Inoltre non ci sono blocchi <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>auto</literal></emphasis>, né <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>allow-hotplug</literal></emphasis> per attivare l'interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> automaticamente in base ad eventi."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13165
msgid "Now you are ready to switch the network configuration."
msgstr "Ora tutto è pronto per commutare tra le configurazioni di rete."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13166
msgid "Let's move your PC to a LAN served by the DHCP.  You bring up the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> (the physical interface) <literal>eth0</literal> by assigning the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name (the logical interface name) <literal>config1</literal> to it by the following."
msgstr "Spostare il PC in una LAN con DHCP. L'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis> (l'interfaccia fisica) <literal>eth0</literal> viene attivata assegnandole il nome di <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione della rete</emphasis> (il nome dell'interfaccia logica) <literal>config1</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13167
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifup eth0=config1\n"
"Password:\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifup eth0=config1\n"
"Password:\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13170
msgid "The interface <literal>eth0</literal> is up, configured by DHCP and connected to LAN."
msgstr "L'interfaccia <literal>eth0</literal> è attiva, configurata con DHCP e connessa alla LAN."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13171
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifdown eth0=config1\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifdown eth0=config1\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13173
msgid "The interface <literal>eth0</literal> is down and disconnected from LAN."
msgstr "L'interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> è disattivata e disconnessa dalla LAN."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13174
msgid "Let's move your PC to a LAN served by the static IP.  You bring up the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> <literal>eth0</literal> by assigning the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name <literal>config2</literal> to it by the following."
msgstr "Spostare il PC in una LAN con IP statico. L'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis> <literal>eth0</literal> viene attivata assegnandole il nome di <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione della rete</emphasis> <literal>config2</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifup eth0=config2\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifup eth0=config2\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13177
msgid "The interface <literal>eth0</literal> is up, configured with static IP and connected to LAN. The additional parameters given as <literal>dns-*</literal> configures \"<literal>/etc/resolv.conf</literal>\" contents.  This \"<literal>/etc/resolv.conf</literal>\" is better manged if the <literal>resolvconf</literal> package is installed."
msgstr "L'interfaccia <literal>eth0</literal> è attiva, configurata con IP statico e connessa alla LAN. I parametri aggiuntivi <literal>dns-*</literal> forniti configurano il contenuto di \"<literal>/etc/resolv.conf</literal>\". Tale file \"<literal>/etc/resolv.conf</literal>\" viene gestito meglio se è installato il pacchetto <literal>resolvconf</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifdown eth0=config2\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifdown eth0=config2\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13180
msgid "The interface <literal>eth0</literal> is down and disconnected from LAN, again."
msgstr "L'interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> è di nuovo disattivata e disconnessa dalla LAN."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13181
msgid "Let's move your PC to a port on BB-modem connected to the PPPoE served service.  You bring up the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> <literal>eth0</literal> by assigning the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name <literal>pppoe</literal> to it by the following."
msgstr "Spostare il PC su una porta di un modem per banda larga connesso ad un servizio PPPoE. L'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis> <literal>eth0</literal> viene attivata assegnandole il nome di <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione della rete</emphasis> <literal>pppoe</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifup eth0=pppoe\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifup eth0=pppoe\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13184
msgid "The interface <literal>eth0</literal> is up, configured with PPPoE connection directly to the ISP."
msgstr "L'interfaccia <literal>eth0</literal> è attiva, configurata per la connessione PPPoE diretta con il fornitore di servizi Internet."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifdown eth0=pppoe\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifdown eth0=pppoe\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13187
msgid "The interface <literal>eth0</literal> is down and disconnected, again."
msgstr "L'interfaccia di rete <literal>eth0</literal> è di nuovo disattivata e disconnessa."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13188
msgid "Let's move your PC to a location without LAN or BB-modem but with POTS and modem.  You bring up the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> <literal>ppp0</literal> by assigning the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name <literal>pots</literal> to it by the following."
msgstr "Spostare il PC in una postazione senza LAN o modem per banda larga, ma con una linea telefonica ed un modem. L'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interfaccia di rete</emphasis> <literal>ppp0</literal> viene attivata assegnandole il nome di <emphasis role=\"strong\">configurazione della rete</emphasis> <literal>pots</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13189
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifup ppp0=pots\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifup ppp0=pots\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13191
msgid "The interface <literal>ppp0</literal> is up and connected to the Internet with PPP."
msgstr "L'interfaccia <literal>ppp0</literal> è attiva e connessa ad Internet con PPP."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13192
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifdown ppp0=pots\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifdown ppp0=pots\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13194
msgid "The interface <literal>ppp0</literal> is down and disconnected from the Internet."
msgstr "L'interfaccia di rete <literal>ppp0</literal> è disattivata e disconnessa da Internet."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13195
msgid "You should check the \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file for the current network configuration state of the <literal>ifupdown</literal> system."
msgstr "Si dovrebbe controllare nel file \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" lo stato attuale della configurazione di rete del sistema <literal>ifupdown</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13197
