msgid "See <literal>ssh-keygen</literal>(1), <literal>ssh-add</literal>(1) and <literal>ssh-agent</literal>(1) for how to use public and secret SSH keys."
msgstr "Per l'uso delle chiavi SSH pubbliche e segrete, vedere <literal>ssh-keygen</literal>(1), <literal>ssh-add</literal>(1) e <literal>ssh-agent</literal>(1)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15836
msgid "Make sure to verify settings by testing the connection.  In case of any problem, use \"<literal>ssh -v</literal>\"."
msgstr "Assicurarsi di verificare le impostazioni testando la connessione. In caso di problemi, usare \"<literal>ssh -v</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15839
msgid "You can change the pass phrase to encrypt local secret SSH keys later with \"<literal>ssh-keygen -p</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si può cambiare successivamente la passphrase per cifrare le chiavi SSH segrete locali  usando \"<literal>ssh-keygen -p</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15842
msgid "You can add options to the entries in \"<literal>~/.ssh/authorized_keys</literal>\" to limit hosts and to run specific commands.  See <literal>sshd</literal>(8) for details."
msgstr "Si possono aggiungere opzioni alle voci in \"<literal>~/.ssh/authorized_keys</literal>\" per limitare gli host e per eseguire comandi specifici. Per i dettagli vedere <literal>sshd</literal>(8)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15844
msgid "The following starts an <literal>ssh</literal>(1) connection from a client."
msgstr "I comandi seguenti avviano una connessione <literal>ssh</literal>(1) da un client."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15846
msgid "List of SSH client startup examples"
msgstr "Elenco di esempi di avvio di client SSH"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15863
msgid "<literal>ssh username@hostname.domain.ext</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>ssh nomeutente@nomehost.dominio.ext</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15866
msgid "connect with default mode"
msgstr "connette nella modalità predefinita"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15871
msgid "<literal>ssh -v username@hostname.domain.ext</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>ssh -v nomeutente@nomehost.dominio.ext</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15874
msgid "connect with default mode with debugging messages"
msgstr "connette nella modalità predefinita con messaggi di debug"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15879
msgid "<literal>ssh -1 username@hostname.domain.ext</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>ssh -1 nomeutente@nomehost.dominio.ext</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15882
msgid "force to connect with SSH version 1"
msgstr "forza la connessione con SSH versione 1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15887
msgid "<literal>ssh -1 -o RSAAuthentication=no -l username hostname.domain.ext</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>ssh -1 -o RSAAuthentication=no -l nomeutente nomehost.dominio.ext</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15890
msgid "force to use password with SSH version 1"
msgstr "forza l'uso di password con SSH versione 1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15895
msgid "<literal>ssh -o PreferredAuthentications=password -l username hostname.domain.ext</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>ssh -o PreferredAuthentications=password -l nomeutente nomehost.dominio.ext</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15898
msgid "force to use password with SSH version 2"
msgstr "forza l'uso di password con SSH versione 2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15904
msgid "If you use the same user name on the local and the remote host, you can eliminate typing \"<literal>username@</literal>\".  Even if you use different user name on the local and the remote host, you can eliminate it using \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\".  For <ulink url=\"&debianaliothservice;\">Debian Alioth service</ulink> with account name \"<literal>foo-guest</literal>\", you set \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\" to contain the following."
msgstr "Se si usa lo stesso nome utente sull'host locale e su quello remoto, si può evitare di digitare la parte \"<literal>nomeutente@</literal>\". Anche se si usa un nome utente diverso nell'host locale rispetto a quello remoto, si può evitare di digitare quella parte usando il file \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\". Per il <ulink url=\"&debianaliothservice;\">servizio Debian Alioth</ulink> con nome account \"<literal>pippo-guest</literal>\", impostre \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\" in modo che contenga quanto segue."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15905
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Host alioth.debian.org svn.debian.org git.debian.org\n"
"    User foo-guest"
msgstr ""
"Host alioth.debian.org svn.debian.org git.debian.org\n"
"    User pippo-guest"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15907
msgid "For the user, <literal>ssh</literal>(1) functions as a smarter and more secure <literal>telnet</literal>(1).  Unlike <literal>telnet</literal> command, <literal>ssh</literal> command does not bomb on the <literal>telnet</literal> escape character (initial default CTRL-])."
msgstr "Per l'utente <literal>ssh</literal>(1) funziona come un  <literal>telnet</literal>(1) più intelligente e più sicuro. A differenza del comando <literal>telnet</literal>, <literal>ssh</literal> non va in crash a seguito del carattere di escape di <literal>telnet</literal> (impostazione predefinita iniziale CTRL-])."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15910
msgid "Port forwarding for SMTP/POP3 tunneling"
msgstr "Forwarding della porta per tunnel SMTP/POP3"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15911
msgid "To establish a pipe to connect to port 25 of <literal>remote-server</literal> from port 4025 of <literal>localhost</literal>, and to port 110 of <literal>remote-server</literal> from port 4110 of <literal>localhost</literal> through <literal>ssh</literal>, execute on the local host as the following."
msgstr "Per stabilire una pipe per connettersi alla porta 25 del <literal>server-remoto</literal> dalla porta 4025 dell'<literal>host locale</literal> e alla porta 110 del <literal>server-remoto</literal> dalla porta 4110 dell'<literal>host locale</literal> attraverso <literal>ssh</literal>, eseguire sull'host locale il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15912
#, no-wrap
msgid "# ssh -q -L 4025:remote-server:25 4110:remote-server:110 username@remote-server"
msgstr "# ssh -q -L 4025:server-remoto:25 4110:server-remoto:110 nomeutente@server-remoto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15913
msgid "This is a secure way to make connections to SMTP/POP3 servers over the Internet.  Set the \"<literal>AllowTcpForwarding</literal>\" entry to \"<literal>yes</literal>\" in \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" of the remote host."
msgstr "Questo è un metodo sicuro di creare connessioni a server SMTP/POP3 in Internet. Impostare nel file \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" dell'host remoto la voce \"<literal>AllowTcpForwarding</literal>\" a \"<literal>yes</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15916
msgid "Connecting without remote passwords"
msgstr "Connettersi senza password remote"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15917
msgid "One can avoid having to remember passwords for remote systems by using \"<literal>RSAAuthentication</literal>\" (SSH-1 protocol) or \"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>\" (SSH-2 protocol)."
msgstr "Si può evitare di doversi ricordare le password per sistemi remoti usando \"<literal>RSAAuthentication</literal>\" (protocollo SSH-1) o \"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>\" (protocollo SSH-2)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15918
msgid "On the remote system, set the respective entries, \"<literal>RSAAuthentication yes</literal>\" or \"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication yes</literal>\", in \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\"."
msgstr "Sul sistema remoto impostare el file \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" le rispettive voci \"<literal>RSAAuthentication yes</literal>\" o \"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication yes</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15919
msgid "Generate authentication keys locally and install the public key on the remote system by the following."
msgstr "Generare localmente le chiavi di autenticazione ed installare la chiave pubblica sul sistema remoto con i comandi seguenti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15923
msgid "\"<literal>RSAAuthentication</literal>\": RSA key for SSH-1 (deprecated because it is superseded.)"
msgstr "\"<literal>RSAAuthentication</literal>\": chiave RSA per SSH-1 (deprecata perché superata)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15927
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ssh-keygen\n"
"$ cat .ssh/identity.pub | ssh user1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""
msgstr ""
"$ ssh-keygen\n"
"$ cat .ssh/identity.pub | ssh utente1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15932
msgid "\"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>\": RSA key for SSH-2"
msgstr "\"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>\": chiave RSA per SSH-2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15936
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ssh-keygen -t rsa\n"
"$ cat .ssh/id_rsa.pub | ssh user1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""
msgstr ""
"$ ssh-keygen -t rsa\n"
"$ cat .ssh/id_rsa.pub | ssh utente1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15941
msgid "\"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>\": DSA key for SSH-2 (deprecated because it is slow.)"
msgstr "\"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>\": chiave DSA per SSH-2 (deprecata perché lenta)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15945
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ssh-keygen -t dsa\n"
"$ cat .ssh/id_dsa.pub | ssh user1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""
msgstr ""
"$ ssh-keygen -t dsa\n"
"$ cat .ssh/id_dsa.pub | ssh utente1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15948
msgid "Use of DSA key for SSH-2 is deprecated because key is smaller and slow. There are no more reasons to work around RSA patent using DSA since it has been expired.  DSA stands for <ulink url=\"&digitalsignaturealgorithm;\">Digital Signature Algorithm</ulink> and slow. Also see <ulink url=\"&dsabfhbb;\">DSA-1571-1</ulink>."
msgstr "L'uso di una chiave DSA per SSH-2 è deprecato perché la chiave è più piccola e più lenta. Non esistono più motivi per aggirare i brevetti RSA usando DSA, dato che essi sono scaduti. DSA sta per <ulink url=\"&digitalsignaturealgorithm;\">Algoritmo di firma digitale (Digital Signature Algotithm</ulink> ed è lento. Vedere anche <ulink url=\"&dsabfhbb;\">DSA-1571-1</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15951
msgid "For \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" to work in SSH-2, you must adjust the settings of \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" to \"<literal>yes</literal>\" in both \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" on the server host and \"<literal>/etc/ssh/ssh_config</literal>\" or \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\" on the client host."
msgstr "Affinché \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" funzioni con SSH-2, si deve impostare la voce \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" a \"<literal>yes</literal>\" in entrambi i file \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" nell'host server e i \"<literal>/etc/ssh/ssh_config</literal>\" o \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\" nell'host client."

