#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20329
msgid "Listing files opened by a process"
msgstr "Elencare i file aperti da un processo"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20330
msgid "You can list all files opened by a process with a process ID (PID), e.g. 1, by the following."
msgstr "È possibile elencare tutti i file aperti da un processo attraverso il suo PID (Identificativo di processo), ad esempio 1, con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20331
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo lsof -p 1"
msgstr "$ sudo lsof -p 1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20332
msgid "PID=1 is usually <literal>init</literal> program."
msgstr "Di solito il processo con PID=1 è il programma <literal>init</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20335
msgid "Tracing program activities"
msgstr "Tenere traccia delle attività di un programma"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20336
msgid "You can trace program activity with <literal>strace</literal>(1), <literal>ltrace</literal>(1), or <literal>xtrace</literal>(1) for system calls and signals, library calls, or communication between X11 client and server."
msgstr "Si può tenere traccia dell'attività di un programma con <literal>strace</literal>(1), <literal>ltrace</literal>(1) o <literal>xtrace</literal>(1) rispettivamente per quello che riguarda chiamate e segnali di sistema, chiamate di libreria o comunicazioni tra client e server X11."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20337
msgid "You can trace system calls of the <literal>ls</literal> command as the following."
msgstr "Si può tenere traccia delle chiamte di sistema del comando <literal>ls</literal> nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20338
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo strace ls"
msgstr "$ sudo strace ls"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20341
msgid "Identification of processes using files or sockets"
msgstr "Identificazione di processi in base a file o socket"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20342
msgid "You can also identify processes using files by <literal>fuser</literal>(1), e.g. for \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Usando <literal>fuser</literal>(1) è anche possibile identificare i processi in base ai file usando, ad esempio per \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20343
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo fuser -v /var/log/mail.log\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"/var/log/mail.log:   root       2946 F.... syslogd"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo fuser -v /var/log/mail.log\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"/var/log/mail.log:   root       2946 F.... syslogd"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20346
msgid "You see that file \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" is open for writing by the <literal>syslogd</literal>(8) command."
msgstr "Come si vede il file \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" è aperto in scrittura dal comando <literal>syslogd</literal>(8)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20347
msgid "You can also identify processes using sockets by <literal>fuser</literal>(1), e.g. for \"<literal>smtp/tcp</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Usando <literal>fuser</literal>(1) si può anche identificare i processi in base ai socket, ad esempio per \"<literal>smtp/tcp</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo fuser -v smtp/tcp\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"smtp/tcp:            Debian-exim   3379 F.... exim4"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo fuser -v smtp/tcp\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"smtp/tcp:            Debian-exim   3379 F.... exim4"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20351
msgid "Now you know your system runs <literal>exim4</literal>(8) to handle <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink> connections to <ulink url=\"&smtp;\">SMTP</ulink> port (25)."
msgstr "Ora si può vedere che sul sistema è in esecuzione <literal>exim4</literal>(8) per gestire le connessioni <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink> alla porta <ulink url=\"&smtp;\">SMTP</ulink> (25)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20354
msgid "Repeating a command with a constant interval"
msgstr "Ripetere un comando ad intervalli costanti"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20355
msgid "<literal>watch</literal>(1) executes a program repeatedly with a constant interval while showing its output in fullscreen."
msgstr "<literal>watch</literal>(1) esegue un programma in modo ripetitivo ad intervalli regolari mostrando il suo output sullo schermo."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20356
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ watch w"
msgstr "$ watch w"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20357
msgid "This displays who is logged on to the system updated every 2 seconds."
msgstr "Questo comando mostra chi è attualmente connesso al sistema in modo aggiornato ogni 2 secondi."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20360
msgid "Repeating a command looping over files"
msgstr "Ripetere un comando su diversi file"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20361
msgid "There are several ways to repeat a command looping over files matching some condition, e.g. matching glob pattern \"<literal>*.ext</literal>\"."
msgstr "Ci sono svariati modi di ripetere uno stesso comando su diversi file che rispondono ad una qualche condizione, ad esempio che corrispondono al modello glob \"<literal>*.ext</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20365
msgid "Shell for-loop method (see <xref linkend=\"_shell_loops\"/>):"
msgstr "Metodo del ciclo for nella shell (vedere <xref linkend=\"_shell_loops\"/>):"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20369
#, no-wrap
msgid "for x in *.ext; do if [ -f \"$x\"]; then command \"$x\" ; fi; done"
msgstr "for x in *.ext; do if [ -f \"$x\"]; then comando \"$x\" ; fi; done"

