#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25673
msgid "Configuration of CVS repository"
msgstr "Configurazione di archivi CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25674
msgid "The following configuration allows commits to the CVS repository only by a member of the \"<literal>src</literal>\" group, and administration of CVS only by a member of the \"<literal>staff</literal>\" group, thus reducing the chance of shooting oneself."
msgstr "La configurazione seguente permette solo ai membri del gruppo \"<literal>src</literal>\" di fare commit nell'archivio CVS e solo ai membri del gruppo \"<literal>staff</literal>\" di amministrare il CVS, riducendo perciò le possibilità di autodanneggiarsi."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25675
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /var/lib; umask 002; mkdir cvs\n"
"# export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project\n"
"# cd $CVSROOT\n"
"# chown root:src .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# cvs -d $CVSROOT init\n"
"# cd CVSROOT\n"
"# chown -R root:staff .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# touch val-tags\n"
"# chmod 664 history val-tags\n"
"# chown root:src history val-tags"
msgstr ""
"# cd /var/lib; umask 002; mkdir cvs\n"
"# export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/progetto\n"
"# cd $CVSROOT\n"
"# chown root:src .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# cvs -d $CVSROOT init\n"
"# cd CVSROOT\n"
"# chown -R root:staff .\n"
"# chmod 2775 .\n"
"# touch val-tags\n"
"# chmod 664 history val-tags\n"
"# chown root:src history val-tags"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25688
msgid "You may restrict creation of new project by changing the owner of \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" directory to \"<literal>root:staff</literal>\" and its permission to \"<literal>3775</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si può limitare la creazione di nuovi progetti modificando il proprietario della directory \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" in \"<literal>root:staff</literal>\" e i suoi permessi in \"<literal>3775</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25692
msgid "Local access to CVS"
msgstr "Accesso locale al CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25693
msgid "The default CVS repository is pointed by \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\".  The following sets up \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" for the local access."
msgstr "L'archivio CVS predefinito è indicato da \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\". Il comando seguente imposta \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" per l'accesso locale."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25694
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project"
msgstr "$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/progetto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25697
msgid "Remote access to CVS with pserver"
msgstr "Accesso remoto a CVS con pserver"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25698
msgid "Many public CVS servers provide read-only remote access to them with account name \"<literal>anonymous</literal>\" via pserver service.  For example, Debian web site contents are maintained by <ulink url=\"&webwmlproject;\">webwml project</ulink> via CVS at Debian alioth service.  The following sets up \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" for the remote access to this CVS repository."
msgstr "Molti server CVS pubblici forniscono accesso remoto solo in lettura all'account \"<literal>anonymous</literal>\" tramite il servizio pserver. I contenuti del sito Debian, per esempio, sono mantenuti dal <ulink url=\"&webwmlproject;\">progetto webwml</ulink> attraverso CVS sul servizio Debian Alioth. Il comando seguente imposta \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" per l'accesso remoto al suo archivio CVS."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25699
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export CVSROOT=:pserver:anonymous@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvsroot/webwml\n"
"$ cvs login"
msgstr ""
"$ export CVSROOT=:pserver:anonymous@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvsroot/webwml\n"
"$ cvs login"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25702
msgid "Since pserver is prone to eavesdropping attack and insecure, write access is usually disable by server administrators."
msgstr "Dato che pserver è esposto ad attacchi di spionaggio ed è insicuro, l'accesso in scrittura è solitamente disabilitato dagli amministratori del server."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25706
msgid "Remote access to CVS with ssh"
msgstr "Accesso remoto a CVS con ssh"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25707
msgid "The following sets up \"<literal>$CVS_RSH</literal>\" and \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" for the remote access to the CVS repository by <ulink url=\"&webwmlproject;\">webwml project</ulink> with SSH."
msgstr "Il comando seguente imposta \"<literal>$CVS_RSH</literal>\" e \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" per l'accesso remoto con SSH all'archivio CVS del <ulink url=\"&webwmlproject;\">progetto webwml</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25708
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export CVS_RSH=ssh\n"
"$ export CVSROOT=:ext:account@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvs/webwml"
msgstr ""
"$ export CVS_RSH=ssh\n"
"$ export CVSROOT=:ext:account@cvs.alioth.debian.org:/cvs/webwml"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25710
msgid "You can also use public key authentication for SSH which eliminates the remote password prompt."
msgstr "Si può anche usare l'autenticazione con chiave pubblica per SSH che elimina la richiesta di inserimento della password remota."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25713
msgid "Importing a new source to CVS"
msgstr "Importare un nuovo sorgente in CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25714 debian-reference.en.xmlt:25950
msgid "Create a new local source tree location at \"<literal>~/path/to/module1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Creare un nuovo albero di sorgenti locale in \"<literal>~/percorso/di/modulo1</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25715 debian-reference.en.xmlt:25951
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ mkdir -p ~/path/to/module1; cd ~/path/to/module1"
msgstr "$ mkdir -p ~/percorso/di/modulo1; cd ~/percorso/di/modulo1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25716 debian-reference.en.xmlt:25952
msgid "Populate a new local source tree under \"<literal>~/path/to/module1</literal>\" with files."
msgstr "Popolare il nuovo albero di sorgenti locale in \"<literal>~/percorso/di/modulo1</literal>\" con i file."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25717
msgid "Import it to CVS with the following parameters."
msgstr "Importarlo nel CVS con i parametri seguenti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25721 debian-reference.en.xmlt:25957
msgid "Module name: \"<literal>module1</literal>\""
msgstr "Nome modulo: \"<literal>modulo1</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25726
msgid "Vendor tag: \"<literal>Main-branch</literal>\" (tag for the entire branch)"
msgstr "Etichetta fornitore: \"<literal>Ramo-principale</literal>\" (etichetta per l'intero ramo)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25731
msgid "Release tag: \"<literal>Release-initial</literal>\" (tag for a specific release)"
msgstr "Etichetta rilascio: \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale</literal>\" (etichetta per un rilascio specifico)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25735
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to/module1\n"
"$ cvs import -m \"Start module1\" module1 Main-branch Release-initial\n"
"$ rm -Rf . # optional"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/percorso/di/modulo1\n"
"$ cvs import -m \"Inizio di modulo1\" Ramo-principale Rilascio-iniziale\n"
"$ rm -Rf . # opzionale"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25740
msgid "File permissions in CVS repository"
msgstr "Permessi dei file negli archivi CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25741
msgid "CVS does not overwrite the current repository file but replaces it with another one.  Thus, write permission to the repository directory is critical.  For every new module for \"<literal>module1</literal>\" in repository at \"<literal>/srv/cvs/project</literal>\", run the following to ensure this condition if needed."
msgstr "CVS non sovrascrive i file attuali nell'archivio, ma li sostituisce con altri. Perciò i permessi di scrittura della directory dell'archivio sono fondamentali. Per ogni nuovo modulo di <literal>modulo1</literal>\" nell'archivio in \"<literal>/srv/cvs/progetto</literal>\", eseguire i comandi seguenti per assicurare che i permessi siano corretti, se necessario."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25742
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /srv/cvs/project\n"
"# chown -R root:src module1\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   module1\n"
"# chmod    2775     module1"
msgstr ""
"# cd /srv/cvs/progetto\n"
"# chown -R root:src modulo1\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   modulo1\n"
"# chmod    2775     modulo1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25748
msgid "Work flow of CVS"
msgstr "Sequenza di azioni tipiche nell'uso di CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25749
msgid "Here is an example of typical work flow using CVS."
msgstr "Ecco un esempio di una sequenza tipica di azioni svolte nell'uso di CVS."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25750
msgid "Check all available modules from CVS project pointed by \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Controllare tutti i moduli disponibili dal progetto CVS a cui punta \"<literal>$CVSROOT</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25751
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs rls\n"
"CVSROOT\n"
"module1\n"
"module2\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ cvs rls\n"
"CVSROOT\n"
"modulo1\n"
"modulo2\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25756
msgid "Checkout \"<literal>module1</literal>\" to its default directory \"<literal>./module1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Fare il checkout di \"<literal>modulo1</literal>\" nella sua directory predefinita \"<literal>./modulo1</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25757
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co module1\n"
"$ cd module1"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/percorso/di\n"
"$ cvs co modulo1\n"
"$ cd modulo1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25760 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26001
msgid "Make changes to the content as needed."
msgstr "Fare i cambiamenti desiderati necessari ai contenuti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25761 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26002
msgid "Check changes by making \"<literal>diff -u [repository] [local]</literal>\" equivalent by the following."
msgstr "Controllare i cambiamenti facendo l'equivalente di \"<literal>diff -u [archivio] [locale]</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25762
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs diff -u"
msgstr "$ cvs diff -u"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25763 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26004
msgid "You find that you broke some file \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" severely but other files are fine."
msgstr "Si scopre, ad esempio, di aver corrotto gravemente un file \"<literal>file_da_ripristinare</literal>\", ma gli altri file sono a posto."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25764
msgid "Overwrite \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" file with the clean copy from CVS by the following."
msgstr "Sovrascrivere \"<literal>file_da_ripristinare</literal>\" con una copia pulita dal CVS con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25765
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -C file_to_undo"
msgstr "$ cvs up -C file_da_ripristinare"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25766
msgid "Save the updated local source tree to CVS by the following."
msgstr "Salvare l'albero dei sorgenti locale aggiornato sul CVS con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25767
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"Describe change\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"Descrivere qui i cambiamenti\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25768
msgid "Create and add \"<literal>file_to_add</literal>\" file to CVS by the following."
msgstr "Creare ed aggiungere il file \"<literal>file_da_aggiungere</literal>\" al CVS con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25769
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ vi file_to_add\n"
"$ cvs add file_to_add\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Added file_to_add\""
msgstr ""
"$ vi file_da_aggiungere\n"
"$ cvs add file_da_aggiungere\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Aggiunto file_da_aggiungere\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25772
msgid "Merge the latest version from CVS by the following."
msgstr "Fondere la versione più recente dal CVS con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25773 debian-reference.en.xmlt:25799
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25774 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26015
msgid "Watch out for lines starting with \"<literal>C filename</literal>\" which indicates conflicting changes."
msgstr "Prestare attenzione alle righe che iniziano con \"<literal>C nomefile</literal>\" che indicano le modifiche che creano conflitti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25775
msgid "Look for unmodified code in \"<literal>.#filename.version</literal>\"."
msgstr "Cercare il codice non modificato in \"<literal>.#nomefile.versione</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25776 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26017
msgid "Search for \"<literal>&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</literal>\" and \"<literal>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</literal>\" in files for conflicting changes."
msgstr "Per trovare le modifiche che creano conflitti cercare \"<literal>&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</literal>\" e \"<literal>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</literal>\" nei file."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25777 debian-reference.en.xmlt:25800
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26018 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26041
msgid "Edit files to fix conflicts as needed."
msgstr "Modificare i file in modo da risolvere i conflitti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25778 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26019
msgid "Add a release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Aggiungere un'etichetta di rilascio \"<literal>Rilascio-1</literal>\" nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25779
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs ci -m \"last commit for Release-1\"\n"
"$ cvs tag Release-1"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs ci -m \"ultimo commit per Rilascio-1\"\n"
"$ cvs tag Rilascio-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25781 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26022
msgid "Edit further."
msgstr "Modificare ulteriormente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25782 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26023
msgid "Remove the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Rimuovere l'etichetta di rilascio \"<literal>Rilascio-1</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25783
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs tag -d Release-1"
msgstr "$ cvs tag -d Rilascio-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25784 debian-reference.en.xmlt:25801
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25808
msgid "Check in changes to CVS by the following."
msgstr "Fare il commit delle modifiche sul CVS con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25785
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"real last commit for Release-1\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"ultimissimo commit per Rilascio-1\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25786
msgid "Re-add the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" to updated CVS HEAD of main by the following."
msgstr "Riaggiungere l'etichetta di rilascio \"<literal>Rilascio-1</literal>\" all'HEAD CVS aggiornato principale con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25787
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs tag Release-1"
msgstr "$ cvs tag Rilascio-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25788
msgid "Create a branch with a sticky branch tag \"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" from the original version pointed by the tag \"<literal>Release-initial</literal>\" and check it out to \"<literal>~/path/to/old</literal>\" directory by the following."
msgstr "Creare un ramo con un'etichetta permanente \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug</literal>\" dalla versione originale a cui punta l'etichetta \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale</literal>\" e farne il checkout nella directory \"<literal>~/percorso/di/vecchio</literal>\" nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25789
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs rtag -b -r Release-initial Release-initial-bugfixes module1\n"
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ cvs co -r Release-initial-bugfixes -d old module1\n"
"$ cd old"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs rtag -b -r Rilascio-iniziale Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug modulo1\n"
"$ cd ~/percorso/di\n"
"$ cvs co -r Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug -d vecchio modulo1\n"
"$ cd vecchio"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25794
msgid "Use \"<literal>-D 2005-12-20</literal>\" (<ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</ulink> date format) instead of \"<literal>-r Release-initial</literal>\" to specify particular date as the branch point."
msgstr "Per specificare una particolare data come punto di ramificazione, usare \"<literal>-D 2005-12-20</literal>\" (formato <ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</ulink> per le date) invece di \"<literal>-r Rilascio-iniziale</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25796
msgid "Work on this local source tree having the sticky tag \"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" which is based on the original version."
msgstr "Lavorare in questo albero locale di sorgenti che ha l'etichetta permanente \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug</literal>\" e che è basato sulla versione originale."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25797 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26038
msgid "Work on this branch by yourself … until someone else joins to this \"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch."
msgstr "Lavorare in questo ramo da soli … fino a che qualcun altro non si aggiunge al ramo \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25798
msgid "Sync with files modified by others on this branch while creating new directories as needed by the following."
msgstr "Fare la sincronizzazione dei file modificati da altri in questo ramo, creando contemporaneamente nuove directory se necessario, con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25802
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"checked into this branch\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"fatto il commit in questo ramo\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25803
msgid "Update the local tree by HEAD of main while removing sticky tag (\"<literal>-A</literal>\") and without keyword expansion (\"<literal>-kk</literal>\") by the following."
msgstr "Aggiornare l'albero locale con l'HEAD del principale, rimuovendo allo stesso tempo l'etichetta permanente (\"<literal>-A</literal>\") e senza espansione delle parole chiave (\"<literal>-kk</literal>\"), con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25804
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d -kk -A"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d -kk -A"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25805
msgid "Update the local tree (content = HEAD of main) by merging from the \"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch and without keyword expansion by the following."
msgstr "Aggiornare l'albero locale (contenuto = HEAD del principale) fondendo dal ramo \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug</literal>\" e senza espansione delle parole chiave con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25806
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs up -d -kk -j Release-initial-bugfixes"
msgstr "$ cvs up -d -kk -j Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25807 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26048
msgid "Fix conflicts with editor."
msgstr "Correggere i conflitti con l'editor."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25809
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ci -m \"merged Release-initial-bugfixes\""
msgstr "$ cvs ci -m \"fusione con Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25810 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26051
msgid "Make archive by the following."
msgstr "Creare un file archivio nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25811 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26052
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ..\n"
"$ mv old old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ tar -cvzf old-module1-bugfixes.tar.gz old-module1-bugfixes\n"
"$ rm -rf old-module1-bugfixes"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ..\n"
"$ mv vecchio vecchio-modulo1-risoluzionebug\n"
"$ tar -cvzf vecchio-modulo1-risoluzionebug.tar.gz vecchio-modulo1-risoluzionebug\n"
"$ rm -rf vecchio-modulo1-risoluzionebug"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25816
msgid "\"<literal>cvs up</literal>\" command can take \"<literal>-d</literal>\" option to create new directories and \"<literal>-P</literal>\" option to prune empty directories."
msgstr "Il comando \"<literal>cvs up</literal>\" accetta l'opzione \"<literal>-d</literal>\" per creare nuove directory e l'opzione \"<literal>-P</literal>\" per eliminare le directory vuote."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25819
msgid "You can checkout only a sub directory of \"<literal>module1</literal>\" by providing its name as \"<literal>cvs co module1/subdir</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si può fare il checkout solamente di una sottodirectory di \"<literal>modulo1</literal>\" fornendo il suo nome come in \"<literal>cvs co modulo1/sottodir</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25822
msgid "Notable options for CVS commands (use as first argument(s) to <literal>cvs</literal>(1))"
msgstr "Opzioni importanti per comandi CVS (da usare come primi argomenti di <literal>cvs</literal>(1))"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25829 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26070
msgid "option"
msgstr "opzione"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25839
msgid "<literal>-n</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>-n</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25842 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26083
msgid "dry run, no effect"
msgstr "esecuzione di prova, nessun effetto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25847
msgid "<literal>-t</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>-t</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25850
msgid "display messages showing steps of cvs activity"
msgstr "visualizza i messaggi che mostrano i passi dell'attività di cvs"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25858
msgid "Latest files from CVS"
msgstr "File più recenti dal CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25859
msgid "To get the latest files from CVS, use \"<literal>tomorrow</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Per ottenere i file più recenti dal CVS usare \"<literal>tomorrow</literal>\" nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25860
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ cvs ex -D tomorrow module_name"
msgstr "$ cvs ex -D tomorrow nome_modulo"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25863
msgid "Administration of CVS"
msgstr "Amministrazione del CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25864
msgid "Add module alias \"<literal>mx</literal>\" to a CVS project (local server) by the following."
msgstr "Aggiungere l'alias \"<literal>mx</literal>\" per un modulo ad un progetto CVS (server locale) usando il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25865
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/project\n"
"$ cvs co CVSROOT/modules\n"
"$ cd CVSROOT\n"
"$ echo \"mx -a module1\" &gt;&gt;modules\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Now mx is an alias for module1\"\n"
"$ cvs release -d ."
msgstr ""
"$ export CVSROOT=/srv/cvs/progetto\n"
"$ cvs co CVSROOT/moduli\n"
"$ cd CVSROOT\n"
"$ echo \"mx -a modulo1\" &gt;&gt;moduli\n"
"$ cvs ci -m \"Ora mx e' un alias per modulo1\"\n"
"$ cvs release -d ."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25871
msgid "Now, you can check out \"<literal>module1</literal>\" (alias: \"<literal>mx</literal>\") from CVS to \"<literal>new</literal>\" directory by the following."
msgstr "Ora si può fare il checkout di \"<literal>modulo1</literal>\" (alias: \"<literal>mx</literal>\") dal CVS alla directory \"<literal>nuova</literal>\" nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25872
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cvs co -d new mx\n"
"$ cd new"
msgstr ""
"$ cvs co -d nuova mx\n"
"$ cd nuova"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25875
msgid "In order to perform above procedure, you should have appropriate file permissions."
msgstr "Per seguire la procedura precedente sono necessari gli adeguati permessi sui file."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25879
msgid "Execution bit for CVS checkout"
msgstr "Bit di esecuzione per il checkout CVS"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25880
msgid "When you checkout files from CVS, their execution permission bit is retained."
msgstr "Quando si fa il checkout di file dal CVS viene mantenuto il loro bit del permesso di esecuzione."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25881
msgid "Whenever you see execution permission problems in a checked out file, e.g. \"<literal>filename</literal>\", change its permission in the corresponding CVS repository by the following to fix it."
msgstr "Ogni volta si incontrano problemi con i permessi di esecuzione di un file di cui si è fatto il checkout, ad esempio \"<literal>nomefile</literal>\", per risolverli cambiare i suoi permessi nell'archivio CVS corrispondente nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25882
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chmod ugo-x filename"
msgstr "# chmod ugo-x nomefile"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25887
msgid "Subversion is a <emphasis role=\"strong\">recent-generation</emphasis> version control system replacing older CVS.  It has most of CVS's features except tags and branches."
msgstr "Subversion è un sistema di controllo delle versioni di <emphasis role=\"strong\">recente generazione</emphasis> che rimpiazza il più vecchio CVS. Ha la maggior parte delle funzionalità di CVS, tranne le etichette ed i rami."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25888
msgid "You need to install <literal>subversion</literal>, <literal>libapache2-svn</literal> and <literal>subversion-tools</literal> packages to set up a Subversion server."
msgstr "Per impostare un server Subversion è necessario installare i pacchetti <literal>subversion</literal>, <literal>libapache2-svn</literal> e <literal>subversion-tools</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25890
msgid "Configuration of Subversion repository"
msgstr "Configurazione di archivi Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25891
msgid "Currently, the <literal>subversion</literal> package does not set up a repository, so one must set it up manually.  One possible location for a repository is in \"<literal>/srv/svn/project</literal>\"."
msgstr "Attualmente il pacchetto <literal>subversion</literal> non imposta un archivio, perciò è necessario farlo manualmente. Una possibile collocazione per un archivio è in \"<literal>/srv/svn/progetto</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25892
msgid "Create a directory by the following."
msgstr "Crear una directory con il comando seguente"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25893
#, no-wrap
msgid "# mkdir -p        /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# mkdir -p        /srv/svn/progetto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25894
msgid "Create the repository database by the following."
msgstr "Creare il database dell'archivio con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25895
#, no-wrap
msgid "# svnadmin create /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# svnadmin create /srv/svn/progetto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25898
msgid "Access to Subversion via Apache2 server"
msgstr "Accedere a Subversion tramite il server Apache2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25899
msgid "If you only access Subversion repository via Apache2 server, you just need to make the repository only writable by the WWW server by the following."
msgstr "Se si accede all'archivio Subversion solamente attraverso il server Apache2, è necessario soltanto rendere l'archivio scrivibile dal server WWW, nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25900
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chown -R www-data:www-data /srv/svn/project"
msgstr "# chown -R www-data:www-data /srv/svn/progetto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25901
msgid "Add (or uncomment) the following in \"<literal>/etc/apache2/mods-available/dav_svn.conf</literal>\" to allow access to the repository via user authentication."
msgstr "Per permettere l'accesso all'archivio tramite autenticazione dell'utente aggiungere (o decommentare) quanto segue in \"<literal>/etc/apache2/mods-available/dav_svn.conf</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25902
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;Location /project&gt;\n"
"  DAV svn\n"
"  SVNPath /srv/svn/project\n"
"  AuthType Basic\n"
"  AuthName \"Subversion repository\"\n"
"  AuthUserFile /etc/subversion/passwd\n"
"&lt;LimitExcept GET PROPFIND OPTIONS REPORT&gt;\n"
"    Require valid-user\n"
"&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;Location /progetto&gt;\n"
"  DAV svn\n"
"  SVNPath /srv/svn/progetto\n"
"  AuthType Basic\n"
"  AuthName \"Subversion repository\"\n"
"  AuthUserFile /etc/subversion/passwd\n"
"&lt;LimitExcept GET PROPFIND OPTIONS REPORT&gt;\n"
"    Require valid-user\n"
"&lt;/LimitExcept&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25912
msgid "Create a user authentication file with the command by the following."
msgstr "Creare un file di autenticazione dell'utente con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25913
#, no-wrap
msgid "# htpasswd2 -c /etc/subversion/passwd some-username"
msgstr "# htpasswd2 -c /etc/subversion/passwd un-qualche-nomeutente"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25914
msgid "Restart Apache2."
msgstr "Riavviare Apache2."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25915
msgid "Your new Subversion repository is accessible at URL \"<literal>http://localhost/project</literal>\" and \"<literal>http://example.com/project</literal>\" from <literal>svn</literal>(1) (assuming your URL of web server is \"<literal>http://example.com/</literal>\")."
msgstr "Il nuovo archivio Subversion è accessibile da <literal>svn</literal>(1) agli URL \"<literal>http://localhost/progetto</literal>\" e \"<literal>http://esempio.com/progetto</literal>\" (assumendo che l'URL del proprio server web sia \"<literal>http://esempio.com/</literal>\")."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25918
msgid "Local access to Subversion by group"
msgstr "Accesso locale a Subversion da parte di un gruppo"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25919
msgid "The following sets up Subversion repository for the local access by a group, e.g. <literal>project</literal>."
msgstr "I comandi seguenti impostano l'archivio Subversion per l'accesso locale da parte di un gruppo, ad esempio <literal>progetto</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25920
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# chmod  2775     /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chown -R root:src /srv/svn/project\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   /srv/svn/project"
msgstr ""
"# chmod  2775     /srv/svn/progetto\n"
"# chown -R root:src /srv/svn/progetto\n"
"# chmod -R ug+rwX   /srv/svn/progetto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25923
msgid "Your new Subversion repository is group accessible at URL \"<literal>file:///localhost/srv/svn/project</literal>\" or \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</literal>\" from <literal>svn</literal>(1) for local users belonging to <literal>project</literal> group.  You must run commands, such as <literal>svn</literal>, <literal>svnserve</literal>, <literal>svnlook</literal>, and <literal>svnadmin</literal> under \"<literal>umask 002</literal>\" to ensure group access."
msgstr "Il nuovo archivio Subversion è accessibile con <literal>svn</literal>(1) per gli utenti locali che appartengono al gruppo <literal>progetto</literal>, all'URL \"<literal>file:///localhost/srv/svn/progetto</literal>\" o \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/progetto</literal>\". Per assicurare l'accesso al gruppo è necessario usare i programmi come <literal>svn</literal>, <literal>svnserve</literal>, <literal>svnlook</literal> e <literal>svnadmin</literal> con \"<literal>umask 002</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25926
msgid "Remote access to Subversion via SSH"
msgstr "Accesso remoto a Subversion con SSH"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25927
msgid "A group accessible Subversion repository is at URL \"<literal>example.com:/srv/svn/project</literal>\" for SSH, you can access it from <literal>svn</literal>(1) at URL \"<literal>svn+ssh://example.com:/srv/svn/project</literal>\"."
msgstr "Se esiste un archivio Subversion accessibile da un gruppo all'URL \"<literal>esempio.com:/srv/svn/progetto</literal>\", si può accedere ad esso con <literal>svn</literal>(1) e SSH all'URL \"<literal>svn+ssh://esempio.com:/srv/svn/progetto</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25930
msgid "Subversion directory structure"
msgstr "Struttura delle directory di Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25931
msgid "Many projects uses directory tree similar to the following for Subversion to compensate its lack of branches and tags."
msgstr "Per compensare la mancanza di rami ed etichette in Subversion, molti progetti usano con esso un albero di directory simile al seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25932
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  ----- module1\n"
"    |   |-- branches\n"
"    |   |-- tags\n"
"    |   |   |-- release-1.0\n"
"    |   |   `-- release-2.0\n"
"    |   |\n"
"    |   `-- trunk\n"
"    |       |-- file1\n"
"    |       |-- file2\n"
"    |       `-- file3\n"
"    |\n"
"    `-- module2"
msgstr ""
"  ----- modulo1\n"
"    |   |-- branches\n"
"    |   |-- tags\n"
"    |   |   |-- rilascio-1.0\n"
"    |   |   `-- rilascio-2.0\n"
"    |   |\n"
"    |   `-- trunk\n"
"    |       |-- file1\n"
"    |       |-- file2\n"
"    |       `-- file3\n"
"    |\n"
"    `-- modulo2"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25945
msgid "You must use \"<literal>svn copy …</literal>\" command to mark branches and tags.  This ensures Subversion to record modification history of files properly and saves storage spaces."
msgstr "Per marcare i rami e le etichette è necessario usare il comando \"<literal>svn copy …</literal>\". Ciò assicura che Subversion regisstri la cronologia dei cambiamenti dei file in maniera corretta e risparma spazio."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25949
msgid "Importing a new source to Subversion"
msgstr "Importare un nuovo sorgente in Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25953
msgid "Import it to Subversion with the following parameters."
msgstr "Importarlo In Subversion con i parametri seguenti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25962
msgid "Subversion site URL: \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</literal>\""
msgstr "URL sito Subversion: \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/progetto</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25967
msgid "Subversion directory: \"<literal>module1/trunk</literal>\""
msgstr "Directory Subversion: \"<literal>modulo1/trunk</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25972
msgid "Subversion tag: \"<literal>module1/tags/Release-initial</literal>\""
msgstr "Etichetta Subversion: \"<literal>modulo1/tags/Rilascio-iniziale</literal>\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25976
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to/module1\n"
"$ svn import file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk -m \"Start module1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-initial"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/percorso/di/modulo1\n"
"$ svn import file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk -m \"Inizo di modulo1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/tags/Rilascio-iniziale"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25979
msgid "Alternatively, by the following."
msgstr "In alternativa usare i comandi seguenti."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25980
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn import ~/path/to/module1 file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk -m \"Start module1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-initial"
msgstr ""
"$ svn import ~/percorso/di/modulo1 file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk -m \"Inizo di modulo1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/tags/Rilascio-iniziale"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25983 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26057
msgid "You can replace URLs such as \"<literal>file:///…</literal>\" by any other URL formats such as \"<literal>http://…</literal>\" and \"<literal>svn+ssh://…</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si possono sostituire gli URL come \"<literal>file:///…</literal>\" con URL in qualsiasi altro formato, come \"<literal>http://…</literal>\" e \"<literal>svn+ssh://…</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25987
msgid "Work flow of Subversion"
msgstr "Sequenza di azioni tipiche nell'uso di Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25988
msgid "Here is an example of typical work flow using Subversion with its native client."
msgstr "Ecco un esempio di una sequenza tipica di azioni svolte nell'uso di Subversion con il suo client nativo."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25990
msgid "Client commands offered by the <literal>git-svn</literal> package may offer alternative work flow of Subversion using the <literal>git</literal> command.  See <xref linkend=\"_git_for_the_subversion_repository\"/>."
msgstr "I comandi client forniti dal pacchetto <literal>git-svn</literal> possono offrire un metodo alternativo di lavoro con Subversion con l'uso del comando <literal>git</literal>. Vedere <xref linkend=\"_git_for_the_subversion_repository\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25992
msgid "Check all available modules from Subversion project pointed by URL \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/project</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Controllare tutti i moduli disponibili dal progetto Subversion a cui punta l'URL \"<literal>file:///srv/svn/progetto</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25993
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn list file:///srv/svn/project\n"
"module1\n"
"module2\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ svn list file:///srv/svn/progetto\n"
"modulo1\n"
"modulo2\n"
"..."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25997
msgid "Checkout \"<literal>module1/trunk</literal>\" to a directory \"<literal>module1</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Fare il checkout di \"<literal>modulo1/trunk</literal>\" in una directory \"<literal>./modulo1</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:25998
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk module1\n"
"$ cd module1"
msgstr ""
"$ cd ~/percorso/di\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk modulo1\n"
"$ cd modulo1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26003
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn diff"
msgstr "$ svn diff"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26005
msgid "Overwrite \"<literal>file_to_undo</literal>\" file with the clean copy from Subversion by the following."
msgstr "Sovrascrivere \"<literal>file_da_ripristinare</literal>\" con una copia pulita da Subversion con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26006
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn revert file_to_undo"
msgstr "$ svn revert file_da_ripristinare"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26007
msgid "Save the updated local source tree to Subversion by the following."
msgstr "Salvare l'albero dei sorgenti locale aggiornato su Subversion con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26008
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"Describe change\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"Descrivere qui i cambiamenti\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26009
msgid "Create and add \"<literal>file_to_add</literal>\" file to Subversion by the following."
msgstr "Creare ed aggiungere il file \"<literal>file_da_aggiungere</literal>\" a Subversion con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26010
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ vi file_to_add\n"
"$ svn add file_to_add\n"
"$ svn ci -m \"Added file_to_add\""
msgstr ""
"$ vi file_da_aggiungere\n"
"$ svn add file_da_aggiungere\n"
"$ svn ci -m \"Aggiunto file_da_aggiungere\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26013
msgid "Merge the latest version from Subversion by the following."
msgstr "Fondere la versione più recente da Subversion con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26014 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26040
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn up"
msgstr "$ svn up"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26016
msgid "Look for unmodified code in, e.g., \"<literal>filename.r6</literal>\", \"<literal>filename.r9</literal>\", and \"<literal>filename.mine</literal>\"."
msgstr "Cercare codice non modificato in, ad esempio \"<literal>nomefile.r6</literal>\", \"<literal>nomefile.r9</literal>\" e \"<literal>nomefile.mio</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26020
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn ci -m \"last commit for Release-1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-1"
msgstr ""
"$ svn ci -m \"ultimo commit per Rilascio-1\"\n"
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/tags/Rilascio-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26024
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn rm file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-1"
msgstr "$ svn rm file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/tags/Rilascio-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26025 debian-reference.en.xmlt:26042
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26049
msgid "Check in changes to Subversion by the following."
msgstr "Fare il commit delle modifiche su Subversion con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26026
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"real last commit for Release-1\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"ultimissimo commit per Rilascio-1\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26027
msgid "Re-add the release tag \"<literal>Release-1</literal>\" from updated Subversion HEAD of trunk by the following."
msgstr "Riaggiungere l'etichetta di rilascio \"<literal>Rilascio-1</literal>\" all'HEAD CVS aggiornato di trunk con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26028
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-1"
msgstr "$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/tags/Rilascio-1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26029
msgid "Create a branch with a path \"<literal>module1/branches/Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" from the original version pointed by the path \"<literal>module1/tags/Release-initial</literal>\" and check it out to \"<literal>~/path/to/old</literal>\" directory by the following."
msgstr "Creare un ramo con percorso \"<literal>modulo1/branches/Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug</literal>\" dalla versione originale a cui punta il percorso \"<literal>modulo1/tags/Rilascio-iniziale</literal>\" e farne il checkout nella directory \"<literal>~/percorso/di/vecchio</literal>\" nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26030
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/project/module1/tags/Release-initial file:///srv/svn/project/module1/branches/Release-initial-bugfixes\n"
"$ cd ~/path/to\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/project/module1/branches/Release-initial-bugfixes old\n"
"$ cd old"
msgstr ""
"$ svn cp file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/tags/Rilascio-initzale file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/branches/Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug\n"
"$ cd ~/percorso/di\n"
"$ svn co file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/branches/Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug vecchio\n"
"$ cd vecchio"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26035
msgid "Use \"<literal>module1/trunk@{2005-12-20}</literal>\" (<ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</ulink> date format) instead of \"<literal>module1/tags/Release-initial</literal>\" to specify particular date as the branch point."
msgstr "Per specificare una particolare data come punto di ramificazione, usare \"<literal>modulo1/trunk@{2005-12-20}</literal>\" (formato <ulink url=\"&isoigab;\">ISO 8601</ulink> per le date) invece di \"<literal>modulo1/tags/Rilascio-iniziale</literal>\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26037
msgid "Work on this local source tree pointing to branch \"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" which is based on the original version."
msgstr "Lavorare in questo albero locale di sorgenti che punta al ramo \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug</literal>\" e che è basato sulla versione originale."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26039
msgid "Sync with files modified by others on this branch by the following."
msgstr "Fare la sincronizzazione con i file in questo ramo modificati da altri, con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26043
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"checked into this branch\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"fatto il commit in questo ramo\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26044
msgid "Update the local tree with HEAD of trunk by the following."
msgstr "Aggiornare l'albero locae con HEAD di trunk nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26045
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn switch file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk"
msgstr "$ svn switch file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26046
msgid "Update the local tree (content = HEAD of trunk) by merging from the \"<literal>Release-initial-bugfixes</literal>\" branch by the following."
msgstr "Aggiornare l'albero locale (contenuto = HEAD di trunk) fondendo dal ramo \"<literal>Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug</literal>\" con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26047
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn merge file:///srv/svn/project/module1/branches/Release-initial-bugfixes"
msgstr "$ svn merge file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/branches/Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26050
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ svn ci -m \"merged Release-initial-bugfixes\""
msgstr "$ svn ci -m \"fusione con Rilascio-iniziale-risoluzionebug\""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26060
msgid "You can checkout only a sub directory of \"<literal>module1</literal>\" by providing its name as \"<literal>svn co file:///srv/svn/project/module1/trunk/subdir module1/subdir</literal>\", etc."
msgstr "Si può fare il checkout solamente di una sottodirectory di \"<literal>modulo1</literal>\" fornendo il suo nome come in \"<literal>svn co file:///srv/svn/progetto/modulo1/trunk/sottodir modulo1/sottodir</literal>\", ecc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26063
msgid "Notable options for Subversion commands (use as first argument(s) to <literal>svn</literal>(1))"
msgstr "Opzioni importanti per comandi Subversion (da usare come primi argomenti di <literal>svn</literal>(1))"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26080
msgid "<literal>--dry-run</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>--dry-run</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26088
msgid "<literal>-v</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>-v</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26091
msgid "display detail messages of svn activity"
msgstr "visualizza messaggi dettagliati sull'attività di svn"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26101
msgid "Git can do everything for both local and remote source code management.  This means that you can record the source code changes without needing network connectivity to the remote repository."
msgstr "Git può fare tutto ciò che riguarda la gestione di codice sorgente, sia in locale sia in remoto. Ciò significa che è possibile registrare i cambiamenti al codice sorgente senza bisogno di connessione di rete all'archivio remoto."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26103
msgid "Configuration of Git client"
msgstr "Configurazione del client Git"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26104
msgid "You may wish to set several global configuration in \"<literal>~/.gitconfig</literal>\" such as your name and email address used by Git by the following."
msgstr "È possibile che si desideri impostare diverse configurazioni globali, come il nome e l'indirizzo di posta elettronica usati da Git, in \"<literal>~/.gitconfig</literal>\" nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ git config --global user.name \"Name Surname\"\n"
"$ git config --global user.email yourname@example.com"
msgstr ""
"$ git config --global user.name \"Nome Cognome\"\n"
"$ git config --global user.email proprionome@esempio.com"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26107
msgid "If you are too used to CVS or Subversion commands, you may wish to set several command aliases by the following."
msgstr "Se si è abituati ai comandi di CVS o Subversion, si potrebbe volere impostare alcuni alias per i comandi nel modo seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ git config --global alias.ci \"commit -a\"\n"
"$ git config --global alias.co checkout"
msgstr ""
"$ git config --global alias.ci \"commit -a\"\n"
"$ git config --global alias.co checkout"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26110
msgid "You can check your global configuration by the following."
msgstr "La configurazione globale può essere controllata con il comando seguente."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26111
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ git config --global --list"
msgstr "$ git config --global --list"

